1
00:01:16,856 --> 00:01:20,587
- You cannot pass!
- Gandalf!

2
00:01:25,466 --> 00:01:30,801
I am a servant of the Secret
Fire, wielder of the flame of Anor.

3
00:01:38,746 --> 00:01:41,509
Go back to the Shadow.

4
00:01:42,415 --> 00:01:46,216
The dark fire will not
avail you, flame of Udun!

5
00:01:50,088 --> 00:01:54,582
You shall not pass!

6
00:02:21,753 --> 00:02:23,414
No! No!

7
00:02:23,622 --> 00:02:25,591
Gandalf!

8
00:02:33,199 --> 00:02:34,927
Fly, you fools.

9
00:02:35,567 --> 00:02:37,432
No!

10
00:02:39,405 --> 00:02:41,463
Gandalf!

11
00:03:50,141 --> 00:03:51,973
Gandalf!

12
00:03:52,978 --> 00:03:55,206
What is it, Mr. Frodo?

13
00:03:57,147 --> 00:03:58,877
Nothing.

14
00:04:06,157 --> 00:04:08,216
Just a dream.

15
00:04:21,404 --> 00:04:22,598
Can you see the bottom?

16
00:04:23,874 --> 00:04:27,002
No! Don't look down, Sam! Just keep going!

17
00:04:37,855 --> 00:04:39,981
Catch it! Grab it, Mr. Frodo!

18
00:04:43,093 --> 00:04:45,062
Mr. Frodo!

19
00:04:47,665 --> 00:04:49,394
I think I've found the bottom.

20
00:04:54,805 --> 00:04:57,797
Bogs and rope, and goodness knows what.

21
00:04:57,973 --> 00:05:01,204
It's not natural. None of it.

22
00:05:04,314 --> 00:05:06,372
- What's in this?
- Nothing.

23
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:08,809
Just a bit of seasoning.

24
00:05:09,418 --> 00:05:12,216
I thought maybe if we was having a
roast chicken one night or something.

25
00:05:12,755 --> 00:05:14,985
Roast chicken?!

26
00:05:15,591 --> 00:05:16,853
You never know.

27
00:05:17,326 --> 00:05:20,262
Sam. My dear Sam.

28
00:05:21,964 --> 00:05:25,901
It's very special, that. It's
the best salt in all the Shire.

29
00:05:27,170 --> 00:05:29,161
It is special.

30
00:05:33,042 --> 00:05:34,942
It's a little bit of home.

31
00:05:38,247 --> 00:05:40,682
We can't leave this here for
someone to follow us down.

32
00:05:41,183 --> 00:05:44,641
Who's gonna follow us down here, Mr. Frodo?

33
00:05:45,487 --> 00:05:49,322
It's a shame, really. Lady
Galadriel gave me that.

34
00:05:50,026 --> 00:05:51,959
Real Elvish rope.

35
00:05:52,829 --> 00:05:55,262
Well, there's nothing for it.
It's one of my knots.

36
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:57,399
Won't come free in a hurry.

37
00:06:06,274 --> 00:06:08,401
Real Elvish rope.

38
00:06:22,557 --> 00:06:27,052
Mordor. The one place in Middle-earth
we don't want to see any closer.

39
00:06:27,228 --> 00:06:29,423
And it's the one place
we're trying to get to.

40
00:06:30,165 --> 00:06:31,927
It's just where we can't get.

41
00:06:33,401 --> 00:06:36,336
Let's face it, Mr. Frodo, we're lost.

42
00:06:38,673 --> 00:06:41,437
I don't think Gandalf meant
for us to come this way.

43
00:06:43,077 --> 00:06:46,377
He didn't mean for a lot of
things to happen, Sam...

44
00:06:47,249 --> 00:06:48,716
...but they did.

45
00:07:01,829 --> 00:07:02,762
Mr. Frodo?

46
00:07:06,701 --> 00:07:08,100
It's the Ring, isn't it?

47
00:07:09,202 --> 00:07:11,670
It's getting heavier.

48
00:07:24,317 --> 00:07:27,048
- What food have we got left?
- Let me see.

49
00:07:27,788 --> 00:07:29,846
Oh, yes. Lovely.

50
00:07:30,024 --> 00:07:32,788
Lembas bread. And look!

51
00:07:35,228 --> 00:07:37,492
More lembas bread.

52
00:07:48,242 --> 00:07:50,209
I don't usually hold with foreign food...

53
00:07:50,411 --> 00:07:53,403
...but this Elvish stuff, it's not bad.

54
00:07:54,281 --> 00:07:57,740
Nothing ever dampens your
spirits, does it, Sam?

55
00:08:03,557 --> 00:08:05,855
Those rain clouds might.

56
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:42,923
This looks strangely familiar.

57
00:08:43,495 --> 00:08:46,020
It's because we've been here before.

58
00:08:46,198 --> 00:08:48,759
We're going in circles.

59
00:08:49,501 --> 00:08:51,366
What is that horrid stink?

60
00:08:51,538 --> 00:08:53,732
I warrant there's a nasty bog nearby.

61
00:08:53,907 --> 00:08:55,841
- Can you smell it?
- Yes.

62
00:08:57,876 --> 00:09:00,106
I can smell it.

63
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:05,783
We're not alone.

64
00:09:19,431 --> 00:09:23,527
The thieves. The thieves.

65
00:09:23,701 --> 00:09:27,661
The filthy little thieves.

66
00:09:28,340 --> 00:09:30,500
Where is it?

67
00:09:30,676 --> 00:09:33,371
Where is it?

68
00:09:34,078 --> 00:09:37,275
They stole it from us.

69
00:09:37,482 --> 00:09:41,681
My precious.

70
00:09:42,553 --> 00:09:45,818
Curse them, we hates them!

71
00:09:45,990 --> 00:09:50,086
It's ours, it is, and we wants it!

72
00:10:45,182 --> 00:10:46,980
This is Sting.

73
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:48,674
You've seen it before...

74
00:10:48,885 --> 00:10:51,354
haven't you, Gollum?

75
00:10:55,426 --> 00:10:58,918
Release him or I'll cut your throat.

76
00:11:14,946 --> 00:11:16,707
It burns!

77
00:11:16,913 --> 00:11:19,211
It burns us!

78
00:11:20,683 --> 00:11:22,150
It freezes!

79
00:11:23,953 --> 00:11:26,217
Nasty Elves twisted it.

80
00:11:26,389 --> 00:11:29,051
- Take it off us!
- Quiet, you!

81
00:11:32,461 --> 00:11:36,727
It's hopeless. Every Orc in
Mordor's going to hear this racket.

82
00:11:36,899 --> 00:11:39,494
- Let's just tie him up and leave him.
- No!

83
00:11:39,769 --> 00:11:43,260
That would kill us! Kill us!

84
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:46,135
It's no more than you deserve!

85
00:11:47,844 --> 00:11:49,869
Maybe he does deserve to die.

86
00:11:52,282 --> 00:11:55,717
But now that I see him, I do pity him.

87
00:11:59,188 --> 00:12:04,024
We be nice to them if they be nice to us.

88
00:12:04,260 --> 00:12:07,024
Take it off us.

89
00:12:10,133 --> 00:12:14,068
We swears to do what you wants.

90
00:12:14,236 --> 00:12:16,171
We swears.

91
00:12:16,472 --> 00:12:18,907
There's no promise you can
make that I can trust.

92
00:12:21,610 --> 00:12:23,338
We swears...

93
00:12:23,611 --> 00:12:28,345
to serve the master of the precious.

94
00:12:29,985 --> 00:12:32,317
We will swear on...

95
00:12:32,488 --> 00:12:34,456
on the precious.

96
00:12:34,623 --> 00:12:36,817
Gollum. Gollum.

97
00:12:36,991 --> 00:12:41,121
The Ring is treacherous. It
will hold you to your word.

98
00:12:41,963 --> 00:12:43,294
Yes...

99
00:12:43,865 --> 00:12:46,356
on the precious.

100
00:12:48,736 --> 00:12:51,171
On the precious.

101
00:12:52,341 --> 00:12:53,831
I don't believe you!

102
00:12:55,878 --> 00:12:59,336
- Get down! I said, down!
- Sam!

103
00:12:59,581 --> 00:13:01,277
He's trying to trick us.

104
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:04,442
If we let him go, he'll
throttle us in our sleep.

105
00:13:15,864 --> 00:13:20,392
- You know the way to Mordor?
- Yes.

106
00:13:23,337 --> 00:13:25,067
You've been there before?

107
00:13:26,073 --> 00:13:27,666
Yes.

108
00:13:38,586 --> 00:13:41,213
You will lead us to the Black Gate.

109
00:13:49,797 --> 00:13:53,664
To the Gate, to the Gate! To
the Gate, the master says. Yes!

110
00:13:53,835 --> 00:13:58,635
No! We won't go back. Not there.
Not to him.

111
00:13:58,806 --> 00:14:03,038
They can't make us. Gollum! Gollum!

112
00:14:03,244 --> 00:14:06,679
But we swore to serve the
master of the precious.

113
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:12,841
No. Ashes and dust and thirst
there is, and pits, pits, pits.

114
00:14:13,020 --> 00:14:15,888
And Orcses, thousands of Orcses.

115
00:14:16,057 --> 00:14:21,187
And always the Great Eye
watching, watching.

116
00:14:24,164 --> 00:14:27,963
Hey! Come back now! Come back!

117
00:14:30,370 --> 00:14:32,600
There! What did I tell you?

118
00:14:32,773 --> 00:14:35,003
He's run off, the old villain.

119
00:14:35,207 --> 00:14:37,698
So much for his promises.

120
00:14:37,911 --> 00:14:39,469
This way, Hobbits.

121
00:14:39,745 --> 00:14:41,770
Follow me!

122
00:14:55,629 --> 00:14:57,028
Merry!

123
00:14:57,998 --> 00:14:59,488
Merry!

124
00:15:05,004 --> 00:15:08,770
You're late. Our master grows impatient.

125
00:15:08,975 --> 00:15:10,772
He wants the Shire-rats now.

126
00:15:11,644 --> 00:15:16,240
I don't take orders from Orc-maggots.

127
00:15:17,283 --> 00:15:20,344
Saruman will have his prize.

128
00:15:20,519 --> 00:15:23,716
We will deliver them.

129
00:15:29,928 --> 00:15:31,293
Merry!

130
00:15:32,030 --> 00:15:33,793
Merry? Wake up.

131
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:39,134
My friend is sick.

132
00:15:39,572 --> 00:15:42,234
He needs water. Please!

133
00:15:43,008 --> 00:15:46,943
Sick, is he? Give him some medicine, boys!

134
00:15:50,182 --> 00:15:51,842
Stop it!

135
00:15:54,052 --> 00:15:56,681
Can't take his draught!

136
00:15:59,357 --> 00:16:01,918
- Leave him alone!
- Why?

137
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:04,826
You want some?

138
00:16:05,563 --> 00:16:08,931
Then keep your mouth shut.

139
00:16:12,337 --> 00:16:14,363
Merry.

140
00:16:15,274 --> 00:16:16,764
Hello, Pip.

141
00:16:18,610 --> 00:16:21,044
- You're hurt.
- I'm fine.

142
00:16:21,212 --> 00:16:23,703
- It was just an act.
- An act?

143
00:16:24,383 --> 00:16:27,250
See? I fooled you too.

144
00:16:29,955 --> 00:16:31,683
Don't worry about me, Pippin.

145
00:16:33,991 --> 00:16:35,982
What is it? What do you smell?

146
00:16:36,961 --> 00:16:38,258
Man-flesh.

147
00:16:40,398 --> 00:16:42,764
They've picked up our trail.

148
00:16:43,868 --> 00:16:44,994
Aragorn.

149
00:16:46,703 --> 00:16:48,534
Let's move!

150
00:17:12,096 --> 00:17:14,621
Their pace has quickened.

151
00:17:15,633 --> 00:17:17,601
They must have caught our scent.

152
00:17:17,769 --> 00:17:19,531
Hurry!

153
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:24,936
Come on, Gimli!

154
00:17:28,779 --> 00:17:31,077
Three days and nights pursuit.

155
00:17:31,249 --> 00:17:34,218
No food. No rest.

156
00:17:34,384 --> 00:17:38,376
And no sign of our quarry,
but what bare rock can tell.

157
00:18:09,786 --> 00:18:12,982
Not idly do the leaves of Lorien fall.

158
00:18:14,324 --> 00:18:16,690
They may yet be alive.

159
00:18:17,528 --> 00:18:20,155
Less than a day ahead of us. Come.

160
00:18:22,766 --> 00:18:25,257
Come, Gimli! We're gaining on them!

161
00:18:25,434 --> 00:18:29,734
I'm wasted on cross-country. We
Dwarves are natural sprinters.

162
00:18:30,273 --> 00:18:33,538
Very dangerous over short distances.

163
00:18:45,288 --> 00:18:47,017
Rohan.

164
00:18:47,189 --> 00:18:49,987
Home of the Horse-lords.

165
00:18:51,192 --> 00:18:53,752
There's something strange at work here.

166
00:18:53,930 --> 00:18:56,898
Some evil gives speed to these creatures.

167
00:18:57,066 --> 00:19:00,035
Sets its will against us.

168
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:08,107
Legolas! What do your Elf-eyes see?

169
00:19:08,277 --> 00:19:10,836
The Uruks turn northeast.

170
00:19:11,681 --> 00:19:13,842
They are taking the Hobbits to Isengard.

171
00:19:14,717 --> 00:19:15,979
Saruman.

172
00:19:24,393 --> 00:19:27,589
The world is changing.

173
00:19:27,762 --> 00:19:33,359
Who now has the strength to stand
against the armies of Isengard...

174
00:19:34,069 --> 00:19:36,799
and Mordor?

175
00:19:38,507 --> 00:19:44,137
To stand against the might
of Sauron and Saruman...

176
00:19:44,311 --> 00:19:47,941
and the union of the two towers?

177
00:19:54,455 --> 00:19:57,424
Together, my Lord Sauron...

178
00:19:57,592 --> 00:20:01,118
we shall rule this Middle-earth.

179
00:20:17,211 --> 00:20:21,478
The Old World will burn
in the fires of industry.

180
00:20:22,049 --> 00:20:25,315
The forests will fall.

181
00:20:27,221 --> 00:20:30,088
A new order will rise.

182
00:20:31,159 --> 00:20:36,061
We will drive the machine of war
with the sword and the spear...

183
00:20:36,230 --> 00:20:40,190
and the iron fists of the Orc.

184
00:20:52,712 --> 00:20:55,943
I want them armed and ready
to march within two weeks!

185
00:20:56,115 --> 00:20:57,742
But, my lord, there are too many!

186
00:20:57,917 --> 00:21:00,943
They cannot all be armed in
time, we don't have the means.

187
00:21:01,121 --> 00:21:04,181
Build a dam, block the stream,
work the furnaces night and day.

188
00:21:04,825 --> 00:21:07,191
We don't have enough
fuel to feed the fires.

189
00:21:08,561 --> 00:21:12,827
The Forest of Fangorn lies on our doorstep.

190
00:21:14,268 --> 00:21:16,599
- Burn it.
- Yes.

191
00:21:17,336 --> 00:21:19,634
We will fight for you.

192
00:21:19,807 --> 00:21:21,775
Swear it.

193
00:21:32,286 --> 00:21:37,052
We will die for Saruman.

194
00:21:38,157 --> 00:21:40,148
The Horse-Men took your lands.

195
00:21:40,326 --> 00:21:44,855
They drove your people into the
hills to scratch a living off rocks.

196
00:21:45,031 --> 00:21:46,464
Murderers!

197
00:21:47,401 --> 00:21:49,492
Take back the lands they stole from you.

198
00:21:49,701 --> 00:21:51,464
Burn every village!

199
00:21:54,707 --> 00:21:59,837
We have only to remove those who oppose us.

200
00:22:00,313 --> 00:22:02,837
It will begin in Rohan.

201
00:22:03,583 --> 00:22:07,109
Too long have these
peasants stood against you.

202
00:22:07,286 --> 00:22:09,083
But no more.

203
00:22:09,255 --> 00:22:11,519
Eothain! Eothain!

204
00:22:13,692 --> 00:22:16,355
You take your sister. You'll
go faster with just two.

205
00:22:16,729 --> 00:22:19,391
Papa says Eothain must not ride Garulf.

206
00:22:19,565 --> 00:22:21,226
He is too big for him.

207
00:22:21,433 --> 00:22:24,403
Listen to me. You must ride
to Edoras and raise the alarm.

208
00:22:24,604 --> 00:22:27,095
- Do you understand me?
- Yes, Mama.

209
00:22:27,405 --> 00:22:30,307
I don't want to leave. I
don't want to go, Mama.

210
00:22:30,476 --> 00:22:34,207
Freda, I will find you there.

211
00:22:39,117 --> 00:22:40,813
Quickly!

212
00:22:47,226 --> 00:22:48,784
Go, child.

213
00:23:01,673 --> 00:23:03,573
Rohan, my lord...

214
00:23:04,041 --> 00:23:06,771
is ready to fall.

215
00:23:18,022 --> 00:23:19,547
Theodred.

216
00:23:19,758 --> 00:23:21,384
Find the king's son!

217
00:23:37,843 --> 00:23:43,873
- Mordor will pay for this.
- These Orcs are not from Mordor.

218
00:23:44,782 --> 00:23:47,615
My Lord Eomer, over here!

219
00:23:56,426 --> 00:23:58,223
He's alive.

220
00:24:29,026 --> 00:24:31,118
Theodred.

221
00:24:44,508 --> 00:24:47,534
Your son is badly wounded, my lord.

222
00:24:47,944 --> 00:24:50,435
He was ambushed by Orcs.

223
00:24:51,981 --> 00:24:55,611
If we don't defend our country,
Saruman will take it by force.

224
00:24:55,986 --> 00:24:58,476
That is a lie.

225
00:25:00,690 --> 00:25:05,490
Saruman the White has ever
been our friend and ally.

226
00:25:07,163 --> 00:25:09,153
Grima.

227
00:25:10,599 --> 00:25:12,534
Grima.

228
00:25:15,070 --> 00:25:16,560
Grima.

229
00:25:17,373 --> 00:25:20,432
Orcs are roaming freely across our lands.

230
00:25:20,843 --> 00:25:24,438
Unchecked. Unchallenged. Killing at will.

231
00:25:25,114 --> 00:25:28,015
Orcs bearing the White Hand of Saruman.

232
00:25:35,857 --> 00:25:41,625
Why do you lay these troubles
on an already troubled mind?

233
00:25:41,830 --> 00:25:44,298
Can you not see?

234
00:25:44,467 --> 00:25:49,494
Your uncle is wearied by your malcontent...

235
00:25:49,705 --> 00:25:52,230
your warmongering.

236
00:25:54,443 --> 00:25:56,412
Warmongering?

237
00:25:56,578 --> 00:25:58,740
How long is it since Saruman bought you?

238
00:25:59,582 --> 00:26:01,946
What was the promised price, Grima?

239
00:26:02,183 --> 00:26:05,778
When all the Men are dead, you will
take your share of the treasure?

240
00:26:18,266 --> 00:26:20,894
Too long have you watched my sister.

241
00:26:21,103 --> 00:26:23,070
Too long have you haunted her steps.

242
00:26:31,145 --> 00:26:35,480
You see much, Eomer, son of Eomund.

243
00:26:35,650 --> 00:26:36,809
Too much.

244
00:26:39,153 --> 00:26:43,954
You are banished forthwith
from the kingdom of Rohan...

245
00:26:44,125 --> 00:26:48,926
and all its domains under pain of death.

246
00:26:49,397 --> 00:26:51,730
You have no authority here.

247
00:26:51,900 --> 00:26:54,367
Your orders mean nothing.

248
00:26:54,903 --> 00:26:58,737
This order does not come from me.

249
00:26:58,906 --> 00:27:01,067
It comes from the king.

250
00:27:01,675 --> 00:27:04,269
He signed it this morning.

251
00:27:35,843 --> 00:27:38,538
Keep breathing. That's the key.

252
00:27:38,778 --> 00:27:40,473
Breathe.

253
00:27:44,585 --> 00:27:48,419
They've run as if the very whips
of their masters were behind them.

254
00:28:04,571 --> 00:28:06,596
We're not going no further...

255
00:28:06,773 --> 00:28:08,763
until we've had a breather.

256
00:28:09,308 --> 00:28:11,277
Get a fire going!

257
00:28:15,347 --> 00:28:16,905
Merry!

258
00:28:17,282 --> 00:28:18,614
Merry!

259
00:28:20,319 --> 00:28:25,519
I think we might have made a
mistake leaving the Shire, Pippin.

260
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:37,195
What's making that noise?

261
00:28:38,770 --> 00:28:40,238
It's the trees.

262
00:28:40,973 --> 00:28:42,031
What?

263
00:28:42,375 --> 00:28:46,209
You remember the Old Forest,
on the borders of Buckland?

264
00:28:46,378 --> 00:28:50,873
Folk used to say there was something in
the water that made the trees grow tall...

265
00:28:51,049 --> 00:28:52,574
and come alive.

266
00:28:52,818 --> 00:28:54,513
Alive?

267
00:28:55,387 --> 00:28:57,083
Trees that could whisper...

268
00:28:58,090 --> 00:29:00,558
talk to each other...

269
00:29:00,727 --> 00:29:02,523
even move.

270
00:29:04,163 --> 00:29:06,394
I'm starving.

271
00:29:06,566 --> 00:29:10,625
We ain't had nothing but maggoty
bread for three stinking days.

272
00:29:11,002 --> 00:29:12,265
Yeah!

273
00:29:12,471 --> 00:29:15,736
Why can't we have some meat?!

274
00:29:18,109 --> 00:29:20,305
What about them?

275
00:29:20,479 --> 00:29:22,378
They're fresh.

276
00:29:23,048 --> 00:29:26,814
They are not for eating.

277
00:29:32,790 --> 00:29:34,759
What about their legs?

278
00:29:34,960 --> 00:29:37,258
They don't need those.

279
00:29:38,730 --> 00:29:41,926
- They look tasty.
- Get back, scum!

280
00:29:43,734 --> 00:29:48,637
The prisoners go to Saruman.
Alive and unspoiled.

281
00:29:49,007 --> 00:29:50,941
Alive?

282
00:29:53,912 --> 00:29:58,177
Why alive? Do they give good sport?

283
00:30:00,586 --> 00:30:03,952
They have something. An Elvish weapon.

284
00:30:04,122 --> 00:30:07,147
The master wants it for the war.

285
00:30:10,061 --> 00:30:11,926
They think we have the Ring.

286
00:30:12,096 --> 00:30:14,529
As soon as they find out
we don't, we're dead.

287
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:18,367
Just a mouthful...

288
00:30:18,536 --> 00:30:19,730
a bit of the flank.

289
00:30:26,544 --> 00:30:30,105
Looks like meat's back on the menu, boys.

290
00:30:36,721 --> 00:30:37,982
Pippin.

291
00:30:38,154 --> 00:30:39,849
Let's go.

292
00:30:48,298 --> 00:30:49,788
Go on.

293
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:51,468
Call for help.

294
00:30:52,869 --> 00:30:53,961
Squeal.

295
00:30:54,171 --> 00:30:57,334
No one's going to save you now.

296
00:31:06,517 --> 00:31:07,915
Pippin!

297
00:31:32,208 --> 00:31:34,699
A red sun rises.

298
00:31:35,211 --> 00:31:38,145
Blood has been spilled this night.

299
00:32:09,311 --> 00:32:11,176
Riders of Rohan...

300
00:32:11,614 --> 00:32:14,048
what news from the Mark?

301
00:32:41,809 --> 00:32:46,212
What business does an Elf, a Man
and a Dwarf have in the Riddermark?

302
00:32:47,015 --> 00:32:48,277
Speak quickly!

303
00:32:48,616 --> 00:32:53,280
Give me your name, horse-master,
and I shall give you mine.

304
00:33:02,431 --> 00:33:04,955
I would cut off your head, Dwarf...

305
00:33:05,401 --> 00:33:07,767
if it stood but a little
higher from the ground.

306
00:33:08,804 --> 00:33:10,863
You would die before your stroke fell.

307
00:33:19,580 --> 00:33:21,480
I am Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

308
00:33:21,817 --> 00:33:26,013
This is Gimli, son of Gloin, and
Legolas of the Woodland Realm.

309
00:33:26,186 --> 00:33:29,417
We are friends of Rohan and
of Theoden, your king.

310
00:33:31,159 --> 00:33:34,924
Theoden no longer
recognizes friend from foe.

311
00:33:35,163 --> 00:33:37,357
Not even his own kin.

312
00:33:41,868 --> 00:33:43,836
Saruman has poisoned the
mind of the king...

313
00:33:44,005 --> 00:33:45,939
and claimed lordship over these lands.

314
00:33:47,909 --> 00:33:50,901
My company are those loyal to Rohan.

315
00:33:51,077 --> 00:33:52,840
And for that, we are banished.

316
00:33:54,915 --> 00:33:58,214
The White Wizard is cunning.

317
00:33:58,885 --> 00:34:01,286
He walks here and there, they say...

318
00:34:01,489 --> 00:34:03,423
as an old man hooded and cloaked.

319
00:34:05,358 --> 00:34:09,125
And everywhere, his spies
slip past our nets.

320
00:34:09,297 --> 00:34:11,527
We are no spies.

321
00:34:11,699 --> 00:34:14,634
We track a party of Uruk-hai
westward across the plain.

322
00:34:14,936 --> 00:34:17,268
They have taken two of our friends captive.

323
00:34:18,072 --> 00:34:20,539
The Uruks are destroyed. We
slaughtered them during the night.

324
00:34:20,708 --> 00:34:23,871
But there were two Hobbits. Did
you see two Hobbits with them?

325
00:34:24,045 --> 00:34:27,012
They would be small. Only
children to your eyes.

326
00:34:30,349 --> 00:34:32,340
We left none alive.

327
00:34:32,985 --> 00:34:35,954
We piled the carcasses and burned them.

328
00:34:41,427 --> 00:34:42,655
Dead?

329
00:34:45,664 --> 00:34:47,360
I am sorry.

330
00:34:52,938 --> 00:34:55,237
Hasufel! Arod!

331
00:34:57,043 --> 00:35:01,706
May these horses bear you to better
fortune than their former masters.

332
00:35:02,916 --> 00:35:04,507
Farewell.

333
00:35:09,722 --> 00:35:11,952
Look for your friends.

334
00:35:12,425 --> 00:35:14,655
But do not trust to hope.

335
00:35:16,362 --> 00:35:18,922
It has forsaken these lands.

336
00:35:19,132 --> 00:35:21,123
We ride north!

337
00:36:11,717 --> 00:36:13,547
It's one of their wee belts.

338
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:18,500
Hiro hyn hÃ®dh ab 'wanath.
(May they find peace after death.)

339
00:36:27,365 --> 00:36:29,391
We failed them.

340
00:36:43,447 --> 00:36:45,608
A Hobbit lay here.

341
00:36:47,518 --> 00:36:49,144
And the other.

342
00:36:59,963 --> 00:37:01,556
They crawled.

343
00:37:05,670 --> 00:37:07,762
Their hands were bound.

344
00:37:19,916 --> 00:37:21,748
Their bonds were cut.

345
00:37:37,233 --> 00:37:39,360
They ran over here.

346
00:37:43,005 --> 00:37:44,199
They were followed.

347
00:37:47,411 --> 00:37:49,139
The belt!

348
00:37:53,050 --> 00:37:54,175
Run!

349
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:59,251
Tracks lead away from the battle...

350
00:38:04,061 --> 00:38:06,153
into Fangorn Forest.

351
00:38:07,063 --> 00:38:08,496
Fangorn?

352
00:38:08,664 --> 00:38:11,293
What madness drove them in there?

353
00:38:29,052 --> 00:38:32,043
Did we lose him? I think we lost him.

354
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:42,197
I'm going to rip out your
filthy little innards!

355
00:38:48,436 --> 00:38:49,425
Come here!

356
00:38:54,943 --> 00:38:57,503
Trees. Climb a tree.

357
00:39:06,822 --> 00:39:08,550
He's gone.

358
00:39:20,635 --> 00:39:22,967
Merry!

359
00:39:34,449 --> 00:39:38,853
Let's put a maggot hole in your belly!

360
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:47,518
Run, Merry!

361
00:39:57,304 --> 00:40:01,639
Little Orcs.

362
00:40:01,809 --> 00:40:04,141
It's talking, Merry. The tree is talking.

363
00:40:04,311 --> 00:40:06,211
Tree?

364
00:40:06,380 --> 00:40:09,373
I am no tree!

365
00:40:09,617 --> 00:40:11,777
I am an Ent.

366
00:40:12,353 --> 00:40:14,480
A tree-herder.

367
00:40:15,056 --> 00:40:17,023
A shepherd of the forest.

368
00:40:17,192 --> 00:40:18,556
Don't talk to it, Merry.

369
00:40:19,059 --> 00:40:20,527
Don't encourage it!

370
00:40:20,728 --> 00:40:24,960
Treebeard, some call me.

371
00:40:25,132 --> 00:40:27,101
And whose side are you on?

372
00:40:27,702 --> 00:40:29,329
Side?

373
00:40:29,536 --> 00:40:32,403
I am on nobody's side...

374
00:40:32,773 --> 00:40:38,110
because nobody's on my side, little Orc.

375
00:40:38,913 --> 00:40:43,543
Nobody cares for the woods anymore.

376
00:40:43,952 --> 00:40:46,351
We're not Orcs! We're Hobbits!

377
00:40:46,519 --> 00:40:48,818
Hobbits?

378
00:40:50,056 --> 00:40:54,925
Never heard of a Hobbit before.

379
00:40:56,128 --> 00:41:00,623
Sounds like Orc mischief to me!

380
00:41:00,800 --> 00:41:02,927
They come with fire.

381
00:41:03,135 --> 00:41:05,695
They come with axes.

382
00:41:05,905 --> 00:41:10,706
Gnawing, biting, breaking,
hacking, burning!

383
00:41:10,911 --> 00:41:14,710
- Destroyers and usurpers! Curse them!
- No!

384
00:41:14,947 --> 00:41:17,780
You don't understand. We're Hobbits!

385
00:41:17,985 --> 00:41:19,782
Halflings!

386
00:41:19,952 --> 00:41:21,045
Shire-folk!

387
00:41:21,255 --> 00:41:23,586
Maybe you are...

388
00:41:23,891 --> 00:41:27,519
and maybe you aren't.

389
00:41:28,628 --> 00:41:32,530
The White Wizard will know.

390
00:41:33,333 --> 00:41:35,266
The White Wizard?

391
00:41:36,802 --> 00:41:38,293
Saruman.

392
00:41:50,882 --> 00:41:52,543
See? See?

393
00:41:52,784 --> 00:41:55,184
We've led you out.

394
00:41:55,353 --> 00:41:57,844
Hurry, Hobbitses. Hurry!

395
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:03,427
Very lucky we find you.

396
00:42:10,101 --> 00:42:11,831
Nice Hobbit.

397
00:42:14,739 --> 00:42:18,005
It's a bog. He's led us into a swamp.

398
00:42:18,177 --> 00:42:20,804
A swamp, yes, yes.

399
00:42:21,579 --> 00:42:26,278
Come, master. We will take you
on safe paths through the mist.

400
00:42:28,621 --> 00:42:32,056
Come, Hobbits! Come! We go quickly.

401
00:42:35,327 --> 00:42:37,956
I found it. I did.

402
00:42:38,164 --> 00:42:40,826
The way through the marshes.

403
00:42:41,032 --> 00:42:44,525
Orcs don't use it. Orcs don't know it.

404
00:42:44,737 --> 00:42:48,797
They go around for miles and miles.

405
00:42:49,007 --> 00:42:50,440
Come quickly.

406
00:42:50,643 --> 00:42:54,702
Soft and quick as shadows we must be.

407
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:59,213
I hate this place. It's too quiet.

408
00:42:59,384 --> 00:43:01,648
There's been no sight nor
sound of a bird for two days.

409
00:43:01,820 --> 00:43:05,186
No, no birdses to eat.

410
00:43:05,422 --> 00:43:09,655
No crunchable birdses.

411
00:43:10,260 --> 00:43:13,128
We are famished! Yes!

412
00:43:13,297 --> 00:43:17,597
Famished we are, precious!

413
00:43:32,550 --> 00:43:34,074
Here.

414
00:43:35,286 --> 00:43:37,277
What does it eats?

415
00:43:37,489 --> 00:43:39,456
Is it tasty?

416
00:43:44,762 --> 00:43:47,356
It tries to chokes us!

417
00:43:47,632 --> 00:43:51,295
We can't eats Hobbit food!

418
00:43:53,003 --> 00:43:57,030
We must starve!

419
00:43:57,206 --> 00:43:59,572
Well, starve, then. And good riddance!

420
00:44:00,344 --> 00:44:02,539
Oh, cruel Hobbit.

421
00:44:02,746 --> 00:44:05,579
It does not care if we be hungry.

422
00:44:05,815 --> 00:44:10,548
Does not care if we should die.

423
00:44:11,188 --> 00:44:14,021
Not like master.

424
00:44:15,391 --> 00:44:17,485
Master cares.

425
00:44:18,661 --> 00:44:20,527
Master knows.

426
00:44:23,000 --> 00:44:24,967
Yes.

427
00:44:25,135 --> 00:44:27,762
Precious.

428
00:44:31,340 --> 00:44:34,969
Once it takes hold of us...

429
00:44:36,847 --> 00:44:41,010
it never lets go.

430
00:44:41,717 --> 00:44:42,878
Don't touch me!

431
00:45:15,351 --> 00:45:17,215
There are dead things!

432
00:45:17,385 --> 00:45:19,148
Dead faces in the water.

433
00:45:23,992 --> 00:45:27,952
All dead. All rotten.

434
00:45:28,463 --> 00:45:32,230
Elves and Men and Orcses.

435
00:45:32,434 --> 00:45:36,063
A great battle long ago.

436
00:45:36,873 --> 00:45:38,601
Dead Marshes.

437
00:45:38,807 --> 00:45:41,538
Yes. Yes, that is their name.

438
00:45:43,246 --> 00:45:44,974
This way.

439
00:45:45,181 --> 00:45:47,945
Don't follow the lights.

440
00:45:49,684 --> 00:45:53,552
Careful now! Or Hobbits go
down to join the dead ones...

441
00:45:53,755 --> 00:45:57,851
and light little candles of their own.

442
00:46:24,052 --> 00:46:25,518
Frodo!

443
00:47:09,996 --> 00:47:14,661
- Gollum?
- Don't follow the lights.

444
00:47:14,835 --> 00:47:16,699
- Gollum!
- Mr. Frodo!

445
00:47:16,869 --> 00:47:18,735
Are you all right?

446
00:47:47,635 --> 00:47:50,603
So bright.

447
00:47:50,804 --> 00:47:54,603
So beautiful.

448
00:47:54,775 --> 00:47:58,643
Our precious.

449
00:48:00,114 --> 00:48:01,603
What did you say?

450
00:48:01,815 --> 00:48:03,976
Master should be resting.

451
00:48:04,150 --> 00:48:08,210
Master needs to keep up his strength.

452
00:48:10,188 --> 00:48:13,454
- Who are you?
- Mustn't ask us. Not its business.

453
00:48:13,626 --> 00:48:15,115
Gollum. Gollum.

454
00:48:15,295 --> 00:48:17,092
Gandalf told me you were
one of the river-folk.

455
00:48:17,262 --> 00:48:21,358
Cold be heart and hand and bone
Cold be travelers far from home

456
00:48:21,534 --> 00:48:23,092
He said your life was a sad story.

457
00:48:23,302 --> 00:48:27,831
They do not see what lies ahead
When sun has failed and moon is dead

458
00:48:28,007 --> 00:48:30,998
You were not so very different
from a Hobbit once.

459
00:48:31,210 --> 00:48:32,938
Were you?

460
00:48:35,181 --> 00:48:37,411
Smeagol.

461
00:48:42,121 --> 00:48:44,646
What did you call me?

462
00:48:45,992 --> 00:48:48,755
That was your name once, wasn't it?

463
00:48:49,329 --> 00:48:51,695
A long time ago.

464
00:48:52,532 --> 00:48:54,693
My name.

465
00:48:55,768 --> 00:48:57,257
My name.

466
00:49:04,143 --> 00:49:06,610
Smeagol.

467
00:49:10,748 --> 00:49:12,376
Black Riders!

468
00:49:12,550 --> 00:49:13,882
Hide! Hide!

469
00:49:24,463 --> 00:49:26,760
Come on, Frodo. Come on!

470
00:49:26,931 --> 00:49:30,561
Quick! They will see us! They will see us!

471
00:49:31,335 --> 00:49:33,998
- I thought they were dead.
- Dead?

472
00:49:34,172 --> 00:49:37,141
No, you cannot kill them. No.

473
00:50:04,302 --> 00:50:05,393
Wraiths!

474
00:50:05,603 --> 00:50:07,798
Wraiths on wings!

475
00:50:15,813 --> 00:50:17,838
They are calling for it.

476
00:50:18,081 --> 00:50:21,608
They are calling for the precious.

477
00:50:23,753 --> 00:50:25,880
Mr. Frodo! It's all right.

478
00:50:26,056 --> 00:50:27,318
I'm here.

479
00:50:43,340 --> 00:50:44,864
Hurry, Hobbits.

480
00:50:45,443 --> 00:50:49,378
The Black Gate is very close.

481
00:50:56,253 --> 00:50:58,117
Orc blood.

482
00:51:08,065 --> 00:51:09,827
These are strange tracks.

483
00:51:11,101 --> 00:51:13,126
The air is so close in here.

484
00:51:14,271 --> 00:51:16,704
This forest is old.

485
00:51:17,507 --> 00:51:19,498
Very old.

486
00:51:21,277 --> 00:51:23,574
Full of memory...

487
00:51:26,181 --> 00:51:28,514
and anger.

488
00:51:34,690 --> 00:51:37,592
The trees are speaking to each other.

489
00:51:37,760 --> 00:51:39,250
Gimli!

490
00:51:39,429 --> 00:51:41,362
Lower your ax.

491
00:51:44,166 --> 00:51:46,931
They have feelings, my friend.

492
00:51:47,469 --> 00:51:49,460
The Elves began it.

493
00:51:49,672 --> 00:51:54,405
Waking up the trees,
teaching them to speak.

494
00:51:54,911 --> 00:51:57,277
Talking trees.

495
00:51:57,914 --> 00:52:00,940
What do trees have to talk about?

496
00:52:01,117 --> 00:52:04,280
Except the consistency
of squirrel droppings.

497
00:52:07,199 --> 00:52:09,050
Aragorn, nad no ennas!
(Aragorn, something is out there!)

498
00:52:15,900 --> 00:52:16,900
Man cenich?
(What do you see?)

499
00:52:18,233 --> 00:52:20,666
The White Wizard approaches.

500
00:52:26,875 --> 00:52:31,175
Do not let him speak. He
will put a spell on us.

501
00:52:40,755 --> 00:52:43,019
We must be quick.

502
00:52:58,606 --> 00:53:02,235
You are tracking the footsteps
of two young Hobbits.

503
00:53:02,811 --> 00:53:04,210
Where are they?

504
00:53:04,378 --> 00:53:07,940
They passed this way the
day before yesterday.

505
00:53:08,115 --> 00:53:12,382
They met someone they did not expect.

506
00:53:12,554 --> 00:53:14,681
Does that comfort you?

507
00:53:14,856 --> 00:53:16,824
Who are you?

508
00:53:18,293 --> 00:53:20,260
Show yourself!

509
00:53:29,170 --> 00:53:31,161
It cannot be.

510
00:53:34,141 --> 00:53:35,108
Forgive me.

511
00:53:36,777 --> 00:53:38,710
I mistook you for Saruman.

512
00:53:39,480 --> 00:53:42,244
I am Saruman.

513
00:53:43,784 --> 00:53:47,652
Or rather, Saruman as he should have been.

514
00:53:48,623 --> 00:53:50,112
You fell.

515
00:53:51,592 --> 00:53:54,117
Through fire...

516
00:53:54,295 --> 00:53:55,592
and water.

517
00:53:57,063 --> 00:53:59,588
From the lowest dungeon
to the highest peak...

518
00:53:59,766 --> 00:54:03,463
I fought with the Balrog of Morgoth.

519
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:22,050
Until at last I threw down my enemy...

520
00:54:22,222 --> 00:54:26,681
and smote his ruin upon the mountainside.

521
00:54:32,699 --> 00:54:35,259
Darkness took me...

522
00:54:36,036 --> 00:54:40,097
and I strayed out of thought and time.

523
00:54:40,873 --> 00:54:43,934
Stars wheeled overhead...

524
00:54:44,210 --> 00:54:48,704
and every day was as long
as a life age of the Earth.

525
00:54:50,849 --> 00:54:52,976
But it was not the end.

526
00:54:53,219 --> 00:54:56,052
I felt life in me again.

527
00:54:57,990 --> 00:55:00,516
I've been sent back...

528
00:55:00,693 --> 00:55:02,251
until my task is done.

529
00:55:02,628 --> 00:55:04,528
Gandalf.

530
00:55:05,197 --> 00:55:07,188
Gandalf?

531
00:55:07,599 --> 00:55:09,396
Yes.

532
00:55:12,204 --> 00:55:14,001
That was what they used to call me.

533
00:55:16,876 --> 00:55:19,139
Gandalf the Grey.

534
00:55:20,480 --> 00:55:22,242
That was my name.

535
00:55:22,414 --> 00:55:23,847
Gandalf.

536
00:55:25,818 --> 00:55:27,878
I am Gandalf the White.

537
00:55:30,922 --> 00:55:33,983
And I come back to you now...

538
00:55:34,159 --> 00:55:36,650
at the turn of the tide.

539
00:55:37,762 --> 00:55:40,731
One stage of your journey is over.
Another begins.

540
00:55:41,500 --> 00:55:44,663
- We must travel to Edoras with all speed.
- Edoras?

541
00:55:45,603 --> 00:55:47,628
That is no short distance!

542
00:55:47,905 --> 00:55:51,137
We hear of trouble in Rohan.
It goes ill with the king.

543
00:55:51,309 --> 00:55:53,402
Yes, and it will not be easily cured.

544
00:55:53,579 --> 00:55:57,014
Then we have run all this way for nothing?

545
00:55:57,181 --> 00:55:59,172
Are we to leave those poor Hobbits here...

546
00:55:59,351 --> 00:56:03,514
in this horrid, dark,
dank tree-infested...?

547
00:56:06,125 --> 00:56:09,288
I mean, charming...

548
00:56:09,460 --> 00:56:12,190
quite charming forest.

549
00:56:12,731 --> 00:56:16,393
It was more than mere chance that
brought Merry and Pippin to Fangorn.

550
00:56:16,601 --> 00:56:20,971
A great power has been sleeping
here for many long years.

551
00:56:21,139 --> 00:56:24,576
The coming of Merry and Pippin will
be like the falling of small stones...

552
00:56:24,742 --> 00:56:28,076
that starts an avalanche in the mountains.

553
00:56:28,246 --> 00:56:31,239
I n one thing you have not
changed, dear friend.

554
00:56:31,416 --> 00:56:35,010
You still speak in riddles.

555
00:56:37,855 --> 00:56:44,260
A thing is about to happen that has
not happened since the Elder Days.

556
00:56:44,427 --> 00:56:48,056
The Ents are going to wake up...

557
00:56:48,599 --> 00:56:53,092
- and find that they are strong.
- Strong?!

558
00:56:53,905 --> 00:56:55,030
Oh, that's good.

559
00:56:55,239 --> 00:56:57,934
So stop your fretting, Master Dwarf.

560
00:56:59,043 --> 00:57:01,273
Merry and Pippin are quite safe.

561
00:57:01,445 --> 00:57:05,039
In fact, they are far safer
than you are about to be.

562
00:57:05,215 --> 00:57:08,947
This new Gandalf's more
grumpy than the old one.

563
00:57:31,242 --> 00:57:32,675
That is one of the Mearas...

564
00:57:32,844 --> 00:57:35,641
unless my eyes are cheated by some spell.

565
00:57:53,262 --> 00:57:55,527
Shadowfax.

566
00:57:58,101 --> 00:58:00,728
He is the lord of all horses...

567
00:58:02,371 --> 00:58:06,239
and has been my friend
through many dangers.

568
00:58:20,489 --> 00:58:24,085
O rowan mine

569
00:58:24,260 --> 00:58:28,061
I saw you shine

570
00:58:28,231 --> 00:58:31,757
Upon a summer's day

571
00:58:32,869 --> 00:58:37,329
Upon your head How golden-red

572
00:58:37,539 --> 00:58:42,271
The crown you bore aloft

573
00:58:42,443 --> 00:58:44,844
Such a beautiful verse.

574
00:58:45,014 --> 00:58:49,916
- Is it much further?
- Bru-ra-hroom. Don't be hasty.

575
00:58:50,085 --> 00:58:53,349
You might call it far, perhaps.

576
00:58:54,255 --> 00:58:58,056
My home lies deep in the forest...

577
00:58:58,260 --> 00:59:02,161
near the roots of the mountain.

578
00:59:03,431 --> 00:59:07,094
I told Gandalf I would keep you safe.

579
00:59:07,335 --> 00:59:11,295
And safe is where I'll keep you.

580
00:59:11,572 --> 00:59:15,942
I believe you will enjoy this next one too.

581
00:59:16,344 --> 00:59:19,336
It's one of my own compositions.

582
00:59:19,514 --> 00:59:20,708
Right.

583
00:59:20,882 --> 00:59:27,014
Beneath the roof of sleeping leaves

584
00:59:27,188 --> 00:59:32,057
And the dreams of trees unfold

585
00:59:32,226 --> 00:59:38,688
When woodland halls are green and cool

586
00:59:38,900 --> 00:59:42,960
And the wind is in the West

587
00:59:43,438 --> 00:59:46,099
Come back to me

588
00:59:46,641 --> 00:59:51,101
Come back to me

589
00:59:51,278 --> 00:59:57,706
And say my land is best

590
01:00:05,159 --> 01:00:08,822
Sleep, little Shirelings.

591
01:00:08,996 --> 01:00:12,592
Heed no nightly noise.

592
01:00:12,800 --> 01:00:16,702
Sleep till morning light.

593
01:00:18,338 --> 01:00:22,503
I have business in the forest.

594
01:00:22,677 --> 01:00:28,206
There are many to call.
Many that must come.

595
01:00:29,449 --> 01:00:34,114
The Shadow lies on Fangorn.

596
01:00:34,288 --> 01:00:40,123
The withering of all woods is drawing near.

597
01:00:49,568 --> 01:00:53,835
The veiling shadow that
glowers in the east takes shape.

598
01:00:54,641 --> 01:00:57,235
Sauron will suffer no rival.

599
01:00:57,677 --> 01:01:01,943
From the summit of Barad-dur,
his Eye watches ceaselessly.

600
01:01:02,114 --> 01:01:05,481
But he is not so mighty yet
that he is above fear.

601
01:01:06,519 --> 01:01:08,487
Doubt ever gnaws at him.

602
01:01:08,655 --> 01:01:11,215
The rumor has reached him.

603
01:01:11,391 --> 01:01:14,360
The heir of Numenor still lives.

604
01:01:15,327 --> 01:01:18,161
Sauron fears you, Aragorn.

605
01:01:19,498 --> 01:01:21,659
He fears what you may become.

606
01:01:22,936 --> 01:01:26,371
And so he'll strike hard and
fast at the world of Men.

607
01:01:26,539 --> 01:01:30,168
He will use his puppet
Saruman to destroy Rohan.

608
01:01:30,342 --> 01:01:31,833
War is coming.

609
01:01:32,012 --> 01:01:35,572
Rohan must defend itself, and
therein lies our first challenge...

610
01:01:35,748 --> 01:01:38,182
for Rohan is weak and ready to fall.

611
01:01:38,351 --> 01:01:42,047
The king's mind is enslaved,
it's an old device of Saruman's.

612
01:01:42,222 --> 01:01:45,315
His hold over King Theoden
is now very strong.

613
01:01:45,492 --> 01:01:50,190
Sauron and Saruman are
tightening the noose.

614
01:01:51,030 --> 01:01:53,157
But for all their cunning...

615
01:01:53,364 --> 01:01:55,889
we have one advantage.

616
01:01:58,070 --> 01:02:00,630
The Ring remains hidden.

617
01:02:01,673 --> 01:02:03,574
And that we should seek to destroy it...

618
01:02:03,742 --> 01:02:06,710
has not yet entered their darkest dreams.

619
01:02:07,313 --> 01:02:10,612
And so the weapon of the enemy
is moving towards Mordor...

620
01:02:10,782 --> 01:02:12,273
in the hands of a Hobbit.

621
01:02:12,451 --> 01:02:16,547
Each day brings it closer
to the fires of Mount Doom.

622
01:02:16,722 --> 01:02:19,349
We must trust now in Frodo.

623
01:02:19,525 --> 01:02:21,356
Everything depends upon speed...

624
01:02:21,527 --> 01:02:24,518
and the secrecy of his quest.

625
01:02:26,498 --> 01:02:29,831
Do not regret your decision to leave him.

626
01:02:30,702 --> 01:02:33,467
Frodo must finish this task alone.

627
01:02:34,206 --> 01:02:36,538
He's not alone.

628
01:02:36,708 --> 01:02:38,403
Sam went with him.

629
01:02:39,077 --> 01:02:40,271
Did he?

630
01:02:40,445 --> 01:02:45,076
Did he, indeed? Good.

631
01:02:45,684 --> 01:02:48,117
Yes, very good.

632
01:02:56,126 --> 01:03:01,030
The Black Gate of Mordor.

633
01:03:03,768 --> 01:03:06,235
Oh, save us.

634
01:03:12,043 --> 01:03:15,273
My old Gaffer would have a thing or
two to say if he could see us now.

635
01:03:17,514 --> 01:03:21,974
Master says to show him
the way into Mordor.

636
01:03:22,152 --> 01:03:25,588
So good Smeagol does, master says so.

637
01:03:25,757 --> 01:03:26,985
I did.

638
01:03:35,766 --> 01:03:37,757
That's it, then.

639
01:03:39,336 --> 01:03:40,634
We can't get past that.

640
01:04:25,815 --> 01:04:27,146
Look!

641
01:04:27,317 --> 01:04:28,784
The gate.

642
01:04:28,952 --> 01:04:30,146
It's opening!

643
01:04:37,594 --> 01:04:39,561
I can see a way down.

644
01:04:40,297 --> 01:04:42,389
Sam, no!

645
01:04:44,601 --> 01:04:45,965
Master!

646
01:06:09,751 --> 01:06:13,277
- I do not ask you to come with me, Sam.
- I know, Mr. Frodo.

647
01:06:14,054 --> 01:06:17,217
I doubt even these Elvish
cloaks will hide us in there.

648
01:06:17,659 --> 01:06:19,523
- Now!
- No!

649
01:06:20,094 --> 01:06:22,063
No! No, master!

650
01:06:22,262 --> 01:06:25,231
They catch you! They catch you!

651
01:06:26,534 --> 01:06:29,094
Don't take it to him.

652
01:06:32,039 --> 01:06:34,769
He wants the precious.

653
01:06:34,943 --> 01:06:37,969
Always he is looking for it.

654
01:06:38,146 --> 01:06:42,047
And the precious is wanting
to go back to him.

655
01:06:42,282 --> 01:06:46,184
But we mustn't let him have it.

656
01:06:52,594 --> 01:06:54,686
No! There's another way.

657
01:06:54,896 --> 01:06:57,557
More secret. A dark way.

658
01:06:57,865 --> 01:07:01,528
- Why haven't you spoken of this before?
- Because master did not ask.

659
01:07:02,003 --> 01:07:03,025
He's up to something.

660
01:07:03,637 --> 01:07:06,231
Are you saying there's
another way into Mordor?

661
01:07:06,407 --> 01:07:09,137
Yes. There's a path...

662
01:07:09,309 --> 01:07:11,800
and some stairs.

663
01:07:12,012 --> 01:07:13,672
And then...

664
01:07:13,847 --> 01:07:17,179
a tunnel.

665
01:07:31,197 --> 01:07:32,994
He's led us this far, Sam.

666
01:07:33,166 --> 01:07:34,565
Mr. Frodo, no.

667
01:07:35,702 --> 01:07:37,168
He's been true to his word.

668
01:07:42,041 --> 01:07:43,235
No.

669
01:07:45,378 --> 01:07:47,005
Lead the way, Smeagol.

670
01:07:47,614 --> 01:07:51,550
Good Smeagol always helps.

671
01:08:25,518 --> 01:08:26,506
Hello?

672
01:08:28,921 --> 01:08:30,979
Treebeard?

673
01:08:31,690 --> 01:08:33,021
Where has he gone?

674
01:08:33,225 --> 01:08:35,659
I had the loveliest dream last night.

675
01:08:36,295 --> 01:08:38,990
There was this large
barrel, full of pipe-weed.

676
01:08:39,164 --> 01:08:41,655
And we smoked all of it. And then...

677
01:08:42,167 --> 01:08:44,101
you were sick.

678
01:08:45,704 --> 01:08:48,537
I'd give anything for a whiff of Old Toby.

679
01:08:52,043 --> 01:08:53,978
Did you hear that?

680
01:09:01,052 --> 01:09:02,452
There it is again.

681
01:09:03,389 --> 01:09:07,984
Something's not right here.
Not right at all.

682
01:09:11,796 --> 01:09:14,730
You just said something... Treeish.

683
01:09:14,899 --> 01:09:18,893
No, I didn't. I was just stretching.

684
01:09:26,444 --> 01:09:28,309
You're taller.

685
01:09:28,846 --> 01:09:30,337
- Who?
- You!

686
01:09:30,515 --> 01:09:32,141
- Than what?
- Than me!

687
01:09:32,650 --> 01:09:34,778
I've always been taller than you.

688
01:09:34,953 --> 01:09:39,582
Pippin, everyone knows I'm the
tall one. You're the short one.

689
01:09:40,457 --> 01:09:41,948
Please, Merry.

690
01:09:42,159 --> 01:09:45,993
You're what? Three-foot-six? At the most?

691
01:09:46,564 --> 01:09:49,398
Whereas me, I'm pushing 3'7".

692
01:09:51,536 --> 01:09:53,800
3'8"!

693
01:09:55,739 --> 01:09:57,570
Three-foot-eight.

694
01:10:00,645 --> 01:10:02,545
You did something.

695
01:10:08,353 --> 01:10:09,944
Merry, don't! Don't drink it!

696
01:10:10,889 --> 01:10:12,354
Merry!

697
01:10:12,555 --> 01:10:14,887
No, Treebeard said that
you shouldn't have any.

698
01:10:15,059 --> 01:10:18,961
- I want some!
- It could well be dangerous!

699
01:10:19,128 --> 01:10:21,289
Give me it back. Merry!

700
01:10:23,132 --> 01:10:24,497
What's happening?!

701
01:10:25,368 --> 01:10:26,836
It's got my leg!

702
01:10:27,171 --> 01:10:28,661
Merry!

703
01:10:48,057 --> 01:10:49,649
Help!

704
01:10:56,432 --> 01:10:58,297
Away with you.

705
01:10:58,469 --> 01:11:00,265
You should not be waking.

706
01:11:00,770 --> 01:11:05,640
Eat earth. Dig deep. Drink water.

707
01:11:06,243 --> 01:11:08,802
Go to sleep.

708
01:11:09,145 --> 01:11:11,011
Away with you.

709
01:11:11,180 --> 01:11:14,479
Come, the forest is waking up.

710
01:11:15,051 --> 01:11:16,984
It isn't safe.

711
01:11:19,655 --> 01:11:23,591
The trees have grown wild and dangerous.

712
01:11:23,760 --> 01:11:26,752
Anger festers in their hearts.

713
01:11:27,630 --> 01:11:29,256
Black are their thoughts.

714
01:11:29,431 --> 01:11:31,957
Strong is their hate.

715
01:11:32,135 --> 01:11:34,899
They will harm you if they can.

716
01:11:35,070 --> 01:11:38,631
There are too few of us now.

717
01:11:38,807 --> 01:11:42,801
Too few of us Ents left to manage them.

718
01:11:43,445 --> 01:11:46,073
Why are there so few of you
when you have lived so long?

719
01:11:46,248 --> 01:11:49,445
- Are there Ent children?
- Bru-ra-hroom.

720
01:11:49,618 --> 01:11:55,251
There have been no Entings for
a terrible long count of years.

721
01:11:55,457 --> 01:12:00,690
- Why is that?
- We lost the Entwives.

722
01:12:00,962 --> 01:12:02,362
Oh, I'm sorry.

723
01:12:02,465 --> 01:12:06,400
- How did they die?
- Die? No.

724
01:12:06,569 --> 01:12:09,800
We lost them.

725
01:12:09,971 --> 01:12:15,034
And now we cannot find them.

726
01:12:15,211 --> 01:12:21,444
I don't suppose you've seen
Entwives in the Shire?

727
01:12:21,837 --> 01:12:24,398
Can't say that I have.

728
01:12:24,942 --> 01:12:26,966
You, Pip?

729
01:12:28,444 --> 01:12:30,845
What do they look like?

730
01:12:33,283 --> 01:12:37,947
I don't remember now.

731
01:12:54,371 --> 01:12:58,273
Edoras and the Golden Hall of Meduseld.

732
01:12:59,042 --> 01:13:01,670
There dwells Theoden, King of Rohan...

733
01:13:02,378 --> 01:13:05,246
whose mind is overthrown.

734
01:13:05,414 --> 01:13:09,680
Saruman's hold over King
Theoden is now very strong.

735
01:13:10,319 --> 01:13:13,483
My lord, your son...

736
01:13:13,657 --> 01:13:15,851
he is dead.

737
01:13:17,360 --> 01:13:19,158
My lord?

738
01:13:20,430 --> 01:13:21,590
Uncle?

739
01:13:28,404 --> 01:13:30,667
Will you not go to him?

740
01:13:33,809 --> 01:13:36,208
Will you do nothing?

741
01:13:36,378 --> 01:13:38,346
Be careful what you say.

742
01:13:38,581 --> 01:13:40,707
Do not look for welcome here.

743
01:14:04,774 --> 01:14:08,904
Oh, he must have died
sometime in the night.

744
01:14:09,110 --> 01:14:11,238
What a tragedy for the king...

745
01:14:11,479 --> 01:14:14,448
to lose his only son and heir.

746
01:14:15,551 --> 01:14:20,078
I understand. His passing
is hard to accept.

747
01:14:20,256 --> 01:14:25,158
Especially now that your
brother has deserted you.

748
01:14:25,326 --> 01:14:26,792
Leave me alone, snake!

749
01:14:28,262 --> 01:14:29,890
Oh, but you are alone.

750
01:14:31,533 --> 01:14:36,300
Who knows what you've
spoken to the darkness...

751
01:14:36,470 --> 01:14:39,929
in the bitter watches of the night...

752
01:14:40,108 --> 01:14:43,770
when all your life seems to shrink.

753
01:14:43,978 --> 01:14:48,176
The walls of your bower
closing in about you.

754
01:14:48,349 --> 01:14:52,911
A hutch to trammel some wild thing in.

755
01:14:55,155 --> 01:14:57,055
So fair.

756
01:14:58,326 --> 01:14:59,690
So cold.

757
01:15:01,462 --> 01:15:03,623
Like a morning of pale spring...

758
01:15:03,832 --> 01:15:07,268
still clinging to winter's chill.

759
01:15:21,048 --> 01:15:23,539
Your words are poison.

760
01:16:56,108 --> 01:16:58,576
You'll find more cheer in a graveyard.

761
01:17:12,925 --> 01:17:16,725
I cannot allow you before Theoden
King so armed, Gandalf Greyhame.

762
01:17:18,230 --> 01:17:20,791
By order of Grima Wormtongue.

763
01:17:38,149 --> 01:17:39,912
Your staff.

764
01:17:43,320 --> 01:17:46,813
You would not part an old
man from his walking stick.

765
01:18:05,609 --> 01:18:08,476
My lord, Gandalf the Grey is coming.

766
01:18:16,787 --> 01:18:18,345
He's a herald of woe.

767
01:18:18,523 --> 01:18:22,960
The courtesy of your hall is
somewhat lessened of late...

768
01:18:24,061 --> 01:18:25,494
Theoden King.

769
01:18:26,197 --> 01:18:28,721
He's not welcome.

770
01:18:29,667 --> 01:18:35,003
Why should I welcome you...

771
01:18:35,506 --> 01:18:39,168
Gandalf Stormcrow?

772
01:18:39,342 --> 01:18:42,641
A just question, my liege.

773
01:18:42,813 --> 01:18:45,680
Late is the hour...

774
01:18:45,849 --> 01:18:49,807
in which this conjurer chooses to appear.

775
01:18:50,621 --> 01:18:52,680
Lathspell I name him.

776
01:18:52,855 --> 01:18:55,756
Ill news is an ill guest.

777
01:18:55,926 --> 01:19:00,488
Be silent. Keep your forked
tongue behind your teeth.

778
01:19:00,663 --> 01:19:02,597
I have not passed through fire and death...

779
01:19:02,699 --> 01:19:05,930
to bandy crooked words with a witless worm.

780
01:19:06,936 --> 01:19:09,029
His staff.

781
01:19:09,238 --> 01:19:13,368
I told you to take the wizard's staff.

782
01:19:16,713 --> 01:19:18,648
Theoden...

783
01:19:19,216 --> 01:19:21,775
son of Thengel...

784
01:19:23,554 --> 01:19:25,920
too long have you sat in the Shadows.

785
01:19:28,891 --> 01:19:32,157
I would stay still if I were you.

786
01:19:32,328 --> 01:19:34,421
Hearken to me!

787
01:19:39,936 --> 01:19:42,063
I release you...

788
01:19:42,270 --> 01:19:44,238
from the spell.

789
01:19:55,784 --> 01:19:58,810
You have no power here...

790
01:19:58,988 --> 01:20:02,617
Gandalf the Grey.

791
01:20:08,029 --> 01:20:13,092
I will draw you, Saruman, as
poison is drawn from a wound.

792
01:20:22,545 --> 01:20:24,069
Wait.

793
01:20:25,515 --> 01:20:29,349
If I go, Theoden dies.

794
01:20:30,051 --> 01:20:32,247
You did not kill me...

795
01:20:32,421 --> 01:20:34,617
you will not kill him.

796
01:20:38,528 --> 01:20:40,222
Rohan is mine.

797
01:20:41,697 --> 01:20:43,028
Be gone.

798
01:21:27,542 --> 01:21:29,668
I know your face.

799
01:21:34,248 --> 01:21:35,511
Eowyn.

800
01:21:37,819 --> 01:21:39,081
Eowyn.

801
01:21:47,360 --> 01:21:48,555
Gandalf?

802
01:21:49,095 --> 01:21:51,962
Breathe the free air again, my friend.

