1303
02:14:07,003 --> 02:14:11,270
So close to achieving its goal.

1304
02:14:14,377 --> 02:14:18,007
For Sauron will have dominion
over all life on this Earth...

1305
02:14:18,181 --> 02:14:22,310
even unto to the ending of the world.

1306
02:14:24,153 --> 02:14:25,984
The time of the Elves...

1307
02:14:26,188 --> 02:14:28,122
is over.

1308
02:14:28,958 --> 02:14:32,554
Do we leave Middle-earth to its fate?

1309
02:14:34,530 --> 02:14:37,795
Do we let them stand alone?

1310
02:14:42,337 --> 02:14:43,703
What news?

1311
02:14:43,873 --> 02:14:46,671
Our scouts report Saruman
has attacked Rohan.

1312
02:14:46,842 --> 02:14:49,710
Theoden's people have fled to Helm's Deep.

1313
02:14:49,880 --> 02:14:53,907
But we must look to our own borders.
Faramir, Orcs are on the move.

1314
02:14:54,082 --> 02:14:56,483
Sauron is marshaling an army.

1315
02:14:56,819 --> 02:14:58,945
Easterlings and Southrons
are at the Black Gate.

1316
02:14:59,122 --> 02:15:02,523
- How many?
- Some thousands. More come every day.

1317
02:15:03,627 --> 02:15:07,186
- Who's covering the river to the north?
- We pulled 500 men at Osgiliath.

1318
02:15:07,395 --> 02:15:10,421
If their city is attacked,
we won't hold it.

1319
02:15:12,568 --> 02:15:14,762
Saruman attacks from Isengard.

1320
02:15:14,936 --> 02:15:17,632
Sauron from Mordor.

1321
02:15:18,940 --> 02:15:22,171
The fight will come to Men on both fronts.

1322
02:15:22,342 --> 02:15:24,037
Gondor is weak.

1323
02:15:24,212 --> 02:15:27,340
Sauron will strike us soon.

1324
02:15:28,083 --> 02:15:29,948
And he will strike hard.

1325
02:15:30,386 --> 02:15:34,481
He knows now we do not have
the strength to repel him.

1326
02:15:48,368 --> 02:15:50,599
My men tell me that you are Orc spies.

1327
02:15:50,771 --> 02:15:53,502
Spies? Now wait just a minute.

1328
02:15:53,675 --> 02:15:55,939
Well, if you're not
spies, then who are you?

1329
02:16:02,817 --> 02:16:04,546
Speak.

1330
02:16:05,652 --> 02:16:08,246
We are Hobbits of the Shire.

1331
02:16:08,588 --> 02:16:11,615
Frodo Baggins is my name,
and this is Samwise Gamgee.

1332
02:16:12,060 --> 02:16:13,550
Your bodyguard?

1333
02:16:13,761 --> 02:16:15,524
His gardener.

1334
02:16:16,163 --> 02:16:18,131
And where is your skulking friend?

1335
02:16:19,667 --> 02:16:21,965
That gangrel creature.

1336
02:16:22,302 --> 02:16:24,270
He had an ill-favored look.

1337
02:16:26,006 --> 02:16:27,905
There was no other.

1338
02:16:32,012 --> 02:16:34,344
We set out from Rivendell
with seven companions.

1339
02:16:37,683 --> 02:16:40,744
One we lost in Moria...

1340
02:16:41,822 --> 02:16:43,345
two were my kin...

1341
02:16:43,523 --> 02:16:47,254
a Dwarf there was also.
And an Elf and two Men.

1342
02:16:47,460 --> 02:16:51,362
Aragorn, son of Arathorn,
and Boromir of Gondor.

1343
02:16:56,370 --> 02:16:58,132
You're a friend of Boromir?

1344
02:17:00,574 --> 02:17:02,064
Yes.

1345
02:17:03,143 --> 02:17:04,235
For my part.

1346
02:17:10,750 --> 02:17:13,684
It will grieve you then
to learn that he is dead.

1347
02:17:15,720 --> 02:17:17,189
Dead?

1348
02:17:17,390 --> 02:17:19,415
How? When?

1349
02:17:19,691 --> 02:17:22,318
As one of his companions, I'd
hoped you would tell me.

1350
02:17:22,661 --> 02:17:26,495
If something has happened to
Boromir, we would have you tell us.

1351
02:17:29,236 --> 02:17:35,697
His horn washed up upon the
riverbank, about six days past.

1352
02:17:35,907 --> 02:17:39,002
It was cloven in two.

1353
02:17:40,611 --> 02:17:44,013
But more than this, I know it in my heart.

1354
02:17:46,051 --> 02:17:47,849
He was my brother.

1355
02:18:37,299 --> 02:18:39,770
Boromir!

1356
02:18:40,304 --> 02:18:42,170
Boromir!

1357
02:18:46,409 --> 02:18:50,175
This city was once the
jewel of our kingdom.

1358
02:18:50,346 --> 02:18:54,010
A place of light and beauty and music.

1359
02:18:54,183 --> 02:18:56,515
And so it shall be once more!

1360
02:18:59,090 --> 02:19:01,718
Let the armies of Mordor know this:

1361
02:19:01,926 --> 02:19:06,293
Never again will the land of
my people fall into enemy hands.

1362
02:19:10,100 --> 02:19:15,765
This city of Osgiliath has
been reclaimed for Gondor!

1363
02:19:16,139 --> 02:19:18,106
- For Gondor!
- For Gondor!

1364
02:19:18,273 --> 02:19:21,106
- For Gondor!
- For Gondor!

1365
02:19:29,818 --> 02:19:32,584
Good speech. Nice and short.

1366
02:19:32,790 --> 02:19:35,690
Leaves more time for drinking!

1367
02:19:35,992 --> 02:19:40,190
Break out the ale! These men are thirsty!

1368
02:19:43,634 --> 02:19:45,795
Remember today, little brother.

1369
02:19:45,968 --> 02:19:48,960
Today, life is good.

1370
02:19:53,141 --> 02:19:54,734
What?

1371
02:19:55,111 --> 02:19:56,577
He's here.

1372
02:19:59,781 --> 02:20:01,613
One moment of peace, can
he not give us that?

1373
02:20:01,783 --> 02:20:02,807
Where is he?

1374
02:20:02,985 --> 02:20:06,442
Where is Gondor's finest?
Where's my first-born?

1375
02:20:07,022 --> 02:20:08,717
Father!

1376
02:20:13,595 --> 02:20:15,961
They say you vanquished the
enemy almost single-handedly.

1377
02:20:16,131 --> 02:20:19,531
They exaggerate. The victory
belongs to Faramir also.

1378
02:20:21,003 --> 02:20:23,904
But for Faramir, this city
would still be standing.

1379
02:20:24,706 --> 02:20:27,004
Were you not entrusted to protect it?

1380
02:20:27,175 --> 02:20:29,200
I would have done, but our
numbers were too few.

1381
02:20:29,378 --> 02:20:31,073
Oh, too few.

1382
02:20:31,581 --> 02:20:33,979
You let the enemy walk in
and take it on a whim.

1383
02:20:36,183 --> 02:20:39,175
Always you cast a poor reflection on me.

1384
02:20:39,388 --> 02:20:41,617
That is not my intent.

1385
02:20:41,823 --> 02:20:45,588
You give him no credit, and
yet he tries to do your will.

1386
02:20:48,962 --> 02:20:51,863
- He loves you, Father.
- Do not trouble me with Faramir...

1387
02:20:52,033 --> 02:20:54,797
I know his uses, and they are few.

1388
02:20:54,969 --> 02:20:58,564
We have more urgent things to speak of.

1389
02:20:59,740 --> 02:21:02,174
Elrond of Rivendell has called a meeting.

1390
02:21:02,343 --> 02:21:05,209
He will not say why, but I
have guessed its purpose.

1391
02:21:05,379 --> 02:21:09,179
It is rumored that the weapon
of the enemy has been found.

1392
02:21:11,418 --> 02:21:13,683
The One Ring.

1393
02:21:16,458 --> 02:21:18,778
Isildur's Bane.

1394
02:21:18,790 --> 02:21:21,120
It has fallen into the
hands of the Elves.

1395
02:21:21,293 --> 02:21:24,924
Everyone will try to claim
it: Men, Dwarves, wizards.

1396
02:21:25,099 --> 02:21:29,228
We cannot let that happen.
This thing must come to Gondor.

1397
02:21:31,039 --> 02:21:33,699
- Gondor.
- It's dangerous, I know.

1398
02:21:33,873 --> 02:21:37,569
Ever the Ring will seek to
corrupt the hearts of lesser Men.

1399
02:21:37,744 --> 02:21:41,647
But you, you are strong.
And our need is great.

1400
02:21:41,816 --> 02:21:47,117
It is our blood which is being
spilled, our people who are dying.

1401
02:21:47,319 --> 02:21:52,347
Sauron is biding his time.
He's massing fresh armies.

1402
02:21:52,558 --> 02:21:54,025
He will return.

1403
02:21:54,227 --> 02:21:57,959
And when he does, we will
be powerless to stop him.

1404
02:21:58,130 --> 02:22:00,691
You must go.

1405
02:22:01,867 --> 02:22:03,960
Bring me back this mighty gift.

1406
02:22:04,802 --> 02:22:10,299
No. My place is here with my people.
Not in Rivendell.

1407
02:22:10,477 --> 02:22:14,174
- Would you deny your own father?
- If there is need to go to Rivendell...

1408
02:22:14,346 --> 02:22:17,315
- send me in his stead.
- You?

1409
02:22:18,518 --> 02:22:20,451
Oh, I see.

1410
02:22:20,619 --> 02:22:24,816
A chance for Faramir, captain
of Gondor, to show his quality.

1411
02:22:25,256 --> 02:22:27,226
I think not.

1412
02:22:27,425 --> 02:22:30,293
I trust this mission only to your brother.

1413
02:22:30,462 --> 02:22:33,362
The one who will not fail me.

1414
02:22:50,449 --> 02:22:53,611
Remember today, little brother.

1415
02:23:12,004 --> 02:23:13,994
Captain Faramir!

1416
02:23:15,273 --> 02:23:17,399
We found the third one.

1417
02:23:28,920 --> 02:23:30,888
You must come with me. Now.

1418
02:23:42,099 --> 02:23:43,191
Down there.

1419
02:23:58,114 --> 02:24:01,014
To enter the Forbidden Pool
bears the penalty of death.

1420
02:24:11,628 --> 02:24:13,118
They wait for my command.

1421
02:24:18,602 --> 02:24:19,693
Shall I shoot?

1422
02:24:20,936 --> 02:24:23,962
The rock and pool Is nice and cool

1423
02:24:24,139 --> 02:24:25,970
So juicy sweet

1424
02:24:26,610 --> 02:24:29,578
Our only wish To catch a fish

1425
02:24:29,746 --> 02:24:32,441
So juicy sweet

1426
02:24:39,422 --> 02:24:40,819
Wait.

1427
02:24:42,325 --> 02:24:45,156
This creature is bound to me.

1428
02:24:45,761 --> 02:24:47,694
And I to him.

1429
02:24:50,966 --> 02:24:52,263
He is our guide.

1430
02:24:57,006 --> 02:24:58,406
Please...

1431
02:24:58,575 --> 02:25:00,439
let me go down to him.

1432
02:25:11,754 --> 02:25:13,415
Smeagol.

1433
02:25:14,423 --> 02:25:16,652
Master is here.

1434
02:25:17,859 --> 02:25:18,985
Come, Smeagol.

1435
02:25:21,863 --> 02:25:24,492
Trust master. Come.

1436
02:25:27,670 --> 02:25:31,503
We must go now?

1437
02:25:31,872 --> 02:25:35,309
Smeagol, you must trust master.

1438
02:25:35,476 --> 02:25:36,875
Follow me. Come on.

1439
02:25:38,111 --> 02:25:39,602
Come.

1440
02:25:42,150 --> 02:25:43,309
Come, Smeagol.

1441
02:25:43,852 --> 02:25:45,876
Nice Smeagol. That's it.

1442
02:25:46,421 --> 02:25:47,911
Come on.

1443
02:25:52,360 --> 02:25:54,021
Don't hurt him!

1444
02:25:54,195 --> 02:25:56,924
Smeagol, don't struggle.
Smeagol, listen to me.

1445
02:25:57,097 --> 02:25:58,396
Master!

1446
02:26:42,816 --> 02:26:47,584
Why does it cry, Smeagol?

1447
02:26:48,855 --> 02:26:51,450
Cruel Men hurts us.

1448
02:26:51,658 --> 02:26:54,628
Master tricksed us.

1449
02:26:54,828 --> 02:26:58,389
Of course he did.

1450
02:26:58,765 --> 02:27:02,462
I told you he was tricksy.

1451
02:27:02,636 --> 02:27:05,662
I told you he was false.

1452
02:27:05,840 --> 02:27:08,536
Master is our friend.

1453
02:27:08,709 --> 02:27:11,075
Our friend.

1454
02:27:11,245 --> 02:27:13,406
Master betrayed us.

1455
02:27:13,581 --> 02:27:16,573
No. Not its business.

1456
02:27:17,650 --> 02:27:20,119
Leave us alone!

1457
02:27:20,287 --> 02:27:22,686
Filthy little Hobbitses!

1458
02:27:22,856 --> 02:27:25,155
They stole it from us!

1459
02:27:25,325 --> 02:27:26,759
No. No.

1460
02:27:27,327 --> 02:27:28,954
What did they steal?

1461
02:27:31,097 --> 02:27:36,433
My precious!

1462
02:27:40,074 --> 02:27:41,700
We have to get out of here.

1463
02:27:42,308 --> 02:27:44,277
You go. Go, now.

1464
02:27:46,880 --> 02:27:48,745
You can do it.

1465
02:27:50,183 --> 02:27:51,650
Use the Ring, Mr. Frodo.

1466
02:27:51,852 --> 02:27:53,614
Just this once.

1467
02:27:53,820 --> 02:27:55,549
Put it on.

1468
02:27:56,022 --> 02:27:58,013
Disappear.

1469
02:27:59,093 --> 02:28:00,150
I can't.

1470
02:28:03,263 --> 02:28:05,494
You were right, Sam.

1471
02:28:06,933 --> 02:28:09,424
You tried to tell me but...

1472
02:28:14,140 --> 02:28:16,301
I'm sorry.

1473
02:28:20,847 --> 02:28:23,715
The Ring's taking me, Sam.

1474
02:28:25,152 --> 02:28:26,779
If I put it on...

1475
02:28:26,986 --> 02:28:29,318
he'll find me.

1476
02:28:30,990 --> 02:28:32,959
He'll see.

1477
02:28:34,193 --> 02:28:36,162
Mr. Frodo...

1478
02:28:41,034 --> 02:28:45,300
So this is the answer to all the riddles.

1479
02:28:47,507 --> 02:28:50,500
Here in the Wild I have you...

1480
02:28:50,677 --> 02:28:52,577
two Halflings...

1481
02:28:52,745 --> 02:28:55,908
and a host of men at my call.

1482
02:28:59,253 --> 02:29:02,710
The Ring of Power within my grasp.

1483
02:29:12,433 --> 02:29:16,164
A chance for Faramir, captain of Gondor...

1484
02:29:17,771 --> 02:29:20,797
to show his quality.

1485
02:29:41,895 --> 02:29:43,486
No!

1486
02:29:46,666 --> 02:29:47,997
Stop it!

1487
02:29:48,167 --> 02:29:49,226
Leave him alone.

1488
02:29:50,570 --> 02:29:53,061
Don't you understand?

1489
02:29:54,375 --> 02:29:56,274
He's got to destroy it!

1490
02:29:56,442 --> 02:29:59,674
That's where we're going, into Mordor.

1491
02:29:59,846 --> 02:30:01,507
To the Mountain of Fire!

1492
02:30:02,583 --> 02:30:05,676
Osgiliath is under attack.
They call for reinforcements.

1493
02:30:05,886 --> 02:30:08,854
Please. It's such a burden.

1494
02:30:11,058 --> 02:30:13,117
Will you not help him?

1495
02:30:14,495 --> 02:30:16,395
Captain?

1496
02:30:17,064 --> 02:30:19,293
Prepare to leave.

1497
02:30:24,237 --> 02:30:26,672
The Ring will go to Gondor.

1498
02:31:26,924 --> 02:31:30,350
Mae carnen, Brego, mellon nÃ®n.
(Well done, Brego, my friend.)

1499
02:31:39,612 --> 02:31:42,240
- He's alive!
- Where is he? Where is he?

1500
02:31:42,415 --> 02:31:45,476
Get out of the way! I'm going to kill him!

1501
02:31:45,685 --> 02:31:49,416
You are the luckiest, the canniest...

1502
02:31:49,622 --> 02:31:53,615
and the most reckless man I ever knew.

1503
02:31:54,327 --> 02:31:55,795
Bless you, laddie.

1504
02:31:56,396 --> 02:31:58,125
Gimli, where is the king?

1505
02:32:06,920 --> 02:32:08,100
Le abdollen.
(You're late.)

1506
02:32:11,912 --> 02:32:13,243
You look terrible.

1507
02:32:40,370 --> 02:32:41,799
Hannon le.
(Thank you.)

1508
02:32:54,987 --> 02:32:57,013
A great host, you say?

1509
02:32:57,224 --> 02:32:59,886
- All Isengard is emptied.
- How many?

1510
02:33:00,560 --> 02:33:03,552
Ten thousand strong at least.

1511
02:33:05,097 --> 02:33:06,531
Ten thousand?

1512
02:33:06,967 --> 02:33:09,458
It is an army bred for a single purpose:

1513
02:33:12,138 --> 02:33:14,265
To destroy the world of Men.

1514
02:33:16,777 --> 02:33:18,768
They will be here by nightfall.

1515
02:33:24,618 --> 02:33:25,915
Let them come!

1516
02:33:27,453 --> 02:33:30,183
I want every man and strong
lad able to bear arms...

1517
02:33:30,389 --> 02:33:33,518
to be ready for battle by nightfall.

1518
02:33:41,701 --> 02:33:44,637
We will cover the causeway
and the gate from above.

1519
02:33:44,805 --> 02:33:47,238
No army has ever breached
the Deeping Wall...

1520
02:33:47,406 --> 02:33:50,137
or set foot inside the Hornburg!

1521
02:33:50,309 --> 02:33:52,709
This is no rabble of mindless Orcs.

1522
02:33:53,313 --> 02:33:55,507
These are Uruk-hai.

1523
02:33:55,682 --> 02:33:59,118
Their armor is thick and
their shields broad.

1524
02:34:00,787 --> 02:34:04,415
I have fought many wars, Master Dwarf.

1525
02:34:04,625 --> 02:34:08,219
I know how to defend my own keep.

1526
02:34:14,834 --> 02:34:18,236
They will break upon this
fortress like water on rock.

1527
02:34:18,405 --> 02:34:23,638
Saruman's hordes will pillage
and burn. We've seen it before.

1528
02:34:23,843 --> 02:34:26,505
Crops can be resown...

1529
02:34:26,680 --> 02:34:29,672
homes rebuilt.

1530
02:34:30,283 --> 02:34:32,843
Within these walls...

1531
02:34:33,253 --> 02:34:34,719
we will outlast them.

1532
02:34:34,922 --> 02:34:37,322
They do not come to destroy
Rohan's crops or villages.

1533
02:34:37,490 --> 02:34:39,014
They come to destroy its people...

1534
02:34:39,158 --> 02:34:41,627
down to the last child.

1535
02:34:42,529 --> 02:34:44,792
What would you have me do?

1536
02:34:44,965 --> 02:34:46,693
Look at my men.

1537
02:34:46,867 --> 02:34:48,595
Their courage hangs by a thread.

1538
02:34:50,804 --> 02:34:55,207
If this is to be our end, then I
would have them make such an end...

1539
02:34:55,375 --> 02:34:58,400
as to be worthy of remembrance.

1540
02:35:02,049 --> 02:35:03,949
Send out riders, my lord.

1541
02:35:04,251 --> 02:35:07,118
You must call for aid.

1542
02:35:10,424 --> 02:35:12,688
And who will come?

1543
02:35:13,093 --> 02:35:14,684
Elves?

1544
02:35:14,861 --> 02:35:16,920
Dwarves?

1545
02:35:17,698 --> 02:35:20,565
We are not so lucky in our friends as you.

1546
02:35:21,400 --> 02:35:23,665
The old alliances are dead.

1547
02:35:24,103 --> 02:35:26,902
- Gondor will answer.
- Gondor?!

1548
02:35:27,074 --> 02:35:29,269
Where was Gondor when the Westfold fell?!

1549
02:35:30,243 --> 02:35:33,474
Where was Gondor when our
enemies closed in around us?!

1550
02:35:33,647 --> 02:35:35,581
Where was Gon...?

1551
02:35:38,251 --> 02:35:40,150
No, my Lord Aragorn...

1552
02:35:41,754 --> 02:35:44,222
we are alone.

1553
02:35:51,097 --> 02:35:52,826
Get the women and children into the caves.

1554
02:35:53,000 --> 02:35:54,262
We need more time to lay provisions...

1555
02:35:54,433 --> 02:35:57,925
There is no time. War is upon us.

1556
02:35:58,204 --> 02:35:59,899
Secure the gate.

