let me go.

1816
03:07:44,075 --> 03:07:45,666
Hurry.

1817
03:07:49,147 --> 03:07:50,546
Faramir!

1818
03:07:50,715 --> 03:07:53,206
You must let me go!

1819
03:07:53,652 --> 03:07:57,110
And those little family of field mice...

1820
03:07:57,289 --> 03:08:00,121
that climb up sometimes, and
they tickle me awfully.

1821
03:08:00,859 --> 03:08:04,157
They're always trying to get
somewhere where they...

1822
03:08:15,340 --> 03:08:18,274
Many of these trees were my friends.

1823
03:08:18,977 --> 03:08:23,606
Creatures I had known from nut and acorn.

1824
03:08:24,782 --> 03:08:25,977
I'm sorry, Treebeard.

1825
03:08:26,150 --> 03:08:28,915
They had voices of their own.

1826
03:08:31,189 --> 03:08:33,713
Saruman.

1827
03:08:34,092 --> 03:08:37,152
A wizard should know better!

1828
03:08:51,376 --> 03:08:55,004
There is no curse in Elvish...

1829
03:08:55,212 --> 03:08:57,875
Entish or the tongues of Men...

1830
03:08:58,049 --> 03:09:00,380
for this treachery.

1831
03:09:01,819 --> 03:09:04,653
Look! The trees! They're moving!

1832
03:09:09,361 --> 03:09:10,555
Where are they going?

1833
03:09:11,095 --> 03:09:14,326
They have business with the Orcs.

1834
03:09:14,799 --> 03:09:19,065
My business is with Isengard tonight...

1835
03:09:19,236 --> 03:09:21,864
with rock and stone.

1836
03:09:45,763 --> 03:09:46,889
Yes.

1837
03:09:47,998 --> 03:09:49,432
Come, my friends.

1838
03:09:50,769 --> 03:09:54,967
The Ents are going to war.

1839
03:09:55,139 --> 03:09:56,903
It is likely...

1840
03:09:57,075 --> 03:10:00,602
that we go to our doom.

1841
03:10:02,013 --> 03:10:04,480
Last march...

1842
03:10:05,015 --> 03:10:07,040
of the Ents.

1843
03:10:55,165 --> 03:10:58,897
Faramir! Orcs have taken the eastern
shore. Their numbers are too great.

1844
03:10:59,069 --> 03:11:01,129
By nightfall we will be overrun.

1845
03:11:03,907 --> 03:11:05,375
Mr. Frodo?

1846
03:11:05,676 --> 03:11:09,772
It's calling to him, Sam.
His Eye is almost on me.

1847
03:11:09,948 --> 03:11:12,439
Hold on, Mr. Frodo. You'll be all right.

1848
03:11:26,798 --> 03:11:28,197
Take them to my father.

1849
03:11:29,766 --> 03:11:32,759
Tell him Faramir sends a mighty gift.

1850
03:11:35,173 --> 03:11:38,199
A weapon that will change
our fortunes in this war.

1851
03:11:39,309 --> 03:11:42,005
Do you want to know what
happened to Boromir?

1852
03:11:42,647 --> 03:11:45,411
You want to know why your brother died?

1853
03:11:45,916 --> 03:11:49,647
He tried to take the Ring from Frodo
after swearing an oath to protect him!

1854
03:11:49,853 --> 03:11:51,754
He tried to kill him!

1855
03:11:51,923 --> 03:11:54,254
The Ring drove your brother mad!

1856
03:11:55,025 --> 03:11:56,890
Watch out!

1857
03:12:07,805 --> 03:12:08,931
Mr. Frodo?

1858
03:12:11,575 --> 03:12:13,406
They're here.

1859
03:12:16,513 --> 03:12:18,981
They've come.

1860
03:12:21,585 --> 03:12:23,486
Nazgul!

1861
03:12:45,542 --> 03:12:47,703
Stay here. Keep out of sight.

1862
03:12:49,513 --> 03:12:51,744
Take cover!

1863
03:13:09,100 --> 03:13:10,657
The fortress is taken.

1864
03:13:11,435 --> 03:13:12,629
It is over.

1865
03:13:12,804 --> 03:13:16,739
You said this fortress would never
fall while your men defend it.

1866
03:13:16,907 --> 03:13:19,843
They still defend it. They
have died defending it.

1867
03:13:22,579 --> 03:13:23,978
They're breaking in!

1868
03:13:26,618 --> 03:13:29,109
They're past the door!

1869
03:13:32,489 --> 03:13:36,620
Is there no other way for the women
and children to get out of the caves?

1870
03:13:39,229 --> 03:13:41,164
Is there no other way?

1871
03:13:42,734 --> 03:13:45,793
There is one passage. It
leads into the mountains.

1872
03:13:46,470 --> 03:13:48,665
But they will not get far.
The Uruk-hai are too many.

1873
03:13:53,543 --> 03:13:55,943
Tell the women and children
to make for the mountain pass.

1874
03:13:56,113 --> 03:13:58,980
- And barricade the entrance!
- So much death.

1875
03:14:01,184 --> 03:14:04,585
What can Men do against such reckless hate?

1876
03:14:09,260 --> 03:14:10,692
Ride out with me.

1877
03:14:14,799 --> 03:14:16,425
Ride out and meet them.

1878
03:14:17,200 --> 03:14:19,361
For death and glory.

1879
03:14:19,537 --> 03:14:20,935
For Rohan.

1880
03:14:22,440 --> 03:14:23,906
For your people.

1881
03:14:24,641 --> 03:14:26,575
The sun is rising.

1882
03:14:31,082 --> 03:14:34,074
Look to my coming at first
light on the fifth day.

1883
03:14:34,252 --> 03:14:35,650
At dawn...

1884
03:14:35,852 --> 03:14:37,513
look to the east.

1885
03:14:41,692 --> 03:14:43,319
Yes.

1886
03:14:45,797 --> 03:14:47,458
Yes.

1887
03:14:48,799 --> 03:14:51,200
The horn of Helm Hammerhand...

1888
03:14:51,369 --> 03:14:54,166
shall sound in the Deep...

1889
03:14:54,604 --> 03:14:56,595
one last time.

1890
03:14:56,773 --> 03:14:58,263
Yes!

1891
03:15:01,311 --> 03:15:05,111
Let this be the hour when
we draw swords together.

1892
03:15:12,924 --> 03:15:14,254
Fell deeds, awake.

1893
03:15:15,459 --> 03:15:16,518
Now for wrath...

1894
03:15:16,727 --> 03:15:20,129
now for ruin and a red dawn.

1895
03:15:27,171 --> 03:15:29,434
Forth Eorlingas!

1896
03:16:17,220 --> 03:16:18,415
Gandalf.

1897
03:16:25,729 --> 03:16:29,393
Theoden King stands alone.

1898
03:16:30,001 --> 03:16:32,162
Not alone.

1899
03:16:32,569 --> 03:16:33,695
Rohirrim!

1900
03:16:39,610 --> 03:16:40,770
Eomer.

1901
03:16:40,944 --> 03:16:43,469
To the king!

1902
03:18:01,125 --> 03:18:02,888
Yes!

1903
03:18:12,036 --> 03:18:15,471
A hit. A fine hit.

1904
03:18:39,996 --> 03:18:42,465
Break the dam!

1905
03:18:42,632 --> 03:18:46,068
Release the river!

1906
03:19:13,431 --> 03:19:16,161
Pippin! Hold on!

1907
03:19:21,439 --> 03:19:24,373
Hold on, little Hobbits.

1908
03:20:05,683 --> 03:20:07,708
What are you doing?

1909
03:20:16,326 --> 03:20:17,851
Where are you going?

1910
03:21:16,052 --> 03:21:17,350
It's me.

1911
03:21:19,889 --> 03:21:22,084
It's your Sam.

1912
03:21:26,430 --> 03:21:29,058
Don't you know your Sam?

1913
03:21:46,717 --> 03:21:50,084
I can't do this, Sam.

1914
03:21:51,021 --> 03:21:52,988
I know.

1915
03:21:54,023 --> 03:21:56,389
It's all wrong.

1916
03:21:57,128 --> 03:21:59,153
By rights, we shouldn't even be here.

1917
03:22:06,569 --> 03:22:08,663
But we are.

1918
03:22:15,078 --> 03:22:18,104
It's like in the great stories, Mr. Frodo.

1919
03:22:18,281 --> 03:22:20,682
The ones that really mattered.

1920
03:22:21,718 --> 03:22:24,710
Full of darkness and danger they were.

1921
03:22:24,922 --> 03:22:27,890
And sometimes you didn't
want to know the end...

1922
03:22:28,058 --> 03:22:30,993
because how could the end be happy?

1923
03:22:33,564 --> 03:22:35,759
How could the world go
back to the way it was...

1924
03:22:35,933 --> 03:22:39,369
when so much bad had happened?

1925
03:22:40,203 --> 03:22:42,103
Victory!

1926
03:22:42,272 --> 03:22:43,831
We have victory!

1927
03:22:44,007 --> 03:22:47,943
But in the end, it's
only a passing thing...

1928
03:22:48,111 --> 03:22:49,442
this shadow.

1929
03:22:49,612 --> 03:22:52,013
Even darkness must pass.

1930
03:22:52,183 --> 03:22:54,879
A new day will come.

1931
03:22:55,084 --> 03:22:59,021
And when the sun shines, it
will shine out the clearer.

1932
03:23:00,958 --> 03:23:03,324
Those were the stories
that stayed with you...

1933
03:23:03,494 --> 03:23:05,256
that meant something.

1934
03:23:05,429 --> 03:23:07,988
Even if you were too
small to understand why.

1935
03:23:09,365 --> 03:23:13,234
But I think, Mr. Frodo, I do understand.

1936
03:23:13,404 --> 03:23:14,961
I know now.

1937
03:23:15,806 --> 03:23:18,001
Folk in those stories...

1938
03:23:18,174 --> 03:23:22,305
had lots of chances of turning
back, only they didn't.

1939
03:23:22,478 --> 03:23:24,709
They kept going...

1940
03:23:25,381 --> 03:23:28,647
because they were holding on to something.

1941
03:23:30,287 --> 03:23:32,584
What are we holding on to, Sam?

1942
03:23:44,468 --> 03:23:48,404
That there's some good in
this world, Mr. Frodo.

1943
03:23:48,672 --> 03:23:51,299
And it's worth fighting for.

1944
03:24:18,235 --> 03:24:22,534
I think at last we understand
one another, Frodo Baggins.

1945
03:24:23,273 --> 03:24:27,233
You know the laws of our
country, the laws of your father.

1946
03:24:27,411 --> 03:24:29,605
If you let them go, your
life will be forfeit.

1947
03:24:33,984 --> 03:24:35,382
Then it is forfeit.

1948
03:24:38,155 --> 03:24:39,850
Release them.

1949
03:24:51,935 --> 03:24:53,995
Stay out of the forest!

1950
03:24:54,171 --> 03:24:55,968
Keep away from the trees!

1951
03:25:46,790 --> 03:25:48,586
Final count...

1952
03:25:48,759 --> 03:25:51,659
- 42.
- 42?

1953
03:25:53,129 --> 03:25:57,897
That's not bad for a
pointy-eared Elvish princeling.

1954
03:25:58,701 --> 03:26:02,364
I myself am sitting pretty on 43.

1955
03:26:06,477 --> 03:26:09,775
- 43.
- He was already dead.

1956
03:26:10,547 --> 03:26:13,038
- He was twitching.
- He was twitching...

1957
03:26:13,217 --> 03:26:17,915
because he's got my ax embedded
in his nervous system!

1958
03:26:20,156 --> 03:26:24,855
- He doesn't look too happy, does he?
- Not too happy at all, Merry.

1959
03:26:25,129 --> 03:26:28,656
Still, I suppose the view would
be quite nice from up there.

1960
03:26:28,832 --> 03:26:31,800
Oh, yes. It's a quality establishment.

1961
03:26:31,968 --> 03:26:34,801
I hear the staff are very good.

1962
03:26:40,477 --> 03:26:42,843
- What are you doing?
- Nothing.

1963
03:26:43,013 --> 03:26:47,279
- The world's back to normal, that's all.
- No, it isn't.

1964
03:26:47,450 --> 03:26:48,679
I'm starving.

1965
03:26:48,886 --> 03:26:51,945
Good luck trying to find
something decent around here.

1966
03:26:52,156 --> 03:26:55,182
Probably dead rats and moldy bread.

1967
03:27:19,183 --> 03:27:21,583
Saruman's storeroom!

1968
03:27:23,953 --> 03:27:26,649
I don't believe it.

1969
03:27:26,856 --> 03:27:28,881
It can't be.

1970
03:27:29,525 --> 03:27:32,426
- It is!
- Longbottom Leaf.

1971
03:27:33,729 --> 03:27:36,028
The finest pipe-weed in South Farthing.

1972
03:27:36,399 --> 03:27:39,425
It's perfect. One barrel each.

1973
03:27:39,602 --> 03:27:40,728
Wait.

1974
03:27:41,471 --> 03:27:42,700
Do you think we should
share it with Treebeard?

1975
03:27:42,872 --> 03:27:44,397
Share it?

1976
03:27:46,243 --> 03:27:48,643
No. No.

1977
03:27:50,147 --> 03:27:51,477
Dead plant and all that.

1978
03:27:51,915 --> 03:27:54,075
Don't think he'd understand.

1979
03:27:55,385 --> 03:27:57,546
Could be a distant relative.

1980
03:27:58,354 --> 03:28:00,845
I get it.

1981
03:28:01,058 --> 03:28:03,855
Don't be hasty.

1982
03:28:04,961 --> 03:28:06,725
Exactly.

1983
03:28:07,798 --> 03:28:10,061
Bar-hrum.

1984
03:28:35,726 --> 03:28:37,022
This is the old sewer.

1985
03:28:37,193 --> 03:28:40,254
Runs right under the river
through to the edge of the city.

1986
03:28:40,430 --> 03:28:42,158
You'll find cover in the woods there.

1987
03:28:43,233 --> 03:28:45,700
Captain Faramir...

1988
03:28:46,335 --> 03:28:48,166
you have shown your quality, sir.

1989
03:28:50,674 --> 03:28:51,970
The very highest.

1990
03:28:52,476 --> 03:28:55,103
The Shire must truly be a
great realm, Master Gamgee...

1991
03:28:55,279 --> 03:28:58,213
where gardeners are held in high honor.

1992
03:28:59,415 --> 03:29:01,384
What road will you take
once you reach the woods?

1993
03:29:02,019 --> 03:29:03,542
Gollum says there's a path...

1994
03:29:03,754 --> 03:29:07,690
near Minas Morgul that climbs
up into the mountains.

1995
03:29:08,157 --> 03:29:09,887
Cirith Ungol?

1996
03:29:13,430 --> 03:29:15,989
- Is that its name?
- No.

1997
03:29:16,165 --> 03:29:17,826
No!

1998
03:29:18,668 --> 03:29:21,661
- Yes.
- Frodo...

1999
03:29:22,039 --> 03:29:25,566
they say a dark terror dwells
in the passes above Minas Morgul.

2000
03:29:26,476 --> 03:29:29,001
- You cannot go that way.
- It is the only way.

2001
03:29:29,345 --> 03:29:35,614
Master says we must go to
Mordor, so we must try.

2002
03:29:37,154 --> 03:29:38,916
I must.

2003
03:29:42,459 --> 03:29:46,020
Go, Frodo. Go with the goodwill of all Men.

2004
03:29:46,195 --> 03:29:48,220
Thank you.

2005
03:30:00,042 --> 03:30:04,173
May death find you quickly
if you bring them to harm.

2006
03:30:16,659 --> 03:30:18,183
Come on, keep up.

2007
03:30:21,665 --> 03:30:24,462
Mr. Frodo didn't mean for
them Rangers to hurt you.

2008
03:30:25,102 --> 03:30:26,933
You know that, don't you?

2009
03:30:27,737 --> 03:30:29,296
He was trying to save you, see?

2010
03:30:29,806 --> 03:30:31,329
Save me?

2011
03:30:31,674 --> 03:30:33,835
So there's no hard feelings.

2012
03:30:34,011 --> 03:30:39,074
- Forgive and forget.
- No, no, no hard feelings.

2013
03:30:39,248 --> 03:30:41,877
Gollum, Gollum.

2014
03:30:42,952 --> 03:30:44,682
Yes, master.

2015
03:30:45,789 --> 03:30:48,621
- Nice Hobbits.
- Very decent of you.

2016
03:30:48,791 --> 03:30:51,090
Very decent, indeed, Gollum.

2017
03:30:56,600 --> 03:31:01,799
Sauron's wrath will be terrible,
his retribution swift.

2018
03:31:08,944 --> 03:31:11,936
The battle for Helm's Deep is over.

2019
03:31:12,615 --> 03:31:16,143
The battle for Middle-earth
is about to begin.

2020
03:31:21,325 --> 03:31:24,761
All our hopes now lie with
two little Hobbits...

2021
03:31:25,728 --> 03:31:28,959
somewhere in the wilderness.

2022
03:31:32,269 --> 03:31:35,670
I wonder if we'll ever be
put into songs or tales.

2023
03:31:35,838 --> 03:31:37,203
What?

2024
03:31:37,373 --> 03:31:41,275
I wonder if people will ever say,
"Let's hear about Frodo and the Ring."

2025
03:31:41,444 --> 03:31:44,709
And they'll say, "Yes! That's
one of my favorite stories."

2026
03:31:44,880 --> 03:31:47,816
"Frodo was really courageous,
wasn't he, Dad?"

2027
03:31:47,984 --> 03:31:49,645
"Yes, my boy.

2028
03:31:49,852 --> 03:31:53,653
The most famousest of Hobbits.
And that's saying a lot."

2029
03:31:53,824 --> 03:31:56,315
Well, you've left out one
of the chief characters:

2030
03:31:56,525 --> 03:31:58,425
"Samwise the Brave."

2031
03:31:58,594 --> 03:32:01,325
I want to hear more about Sam.

2032
03:32:05,635 --> 03:32:08,627
Frodo wouldn't have got far without Sam.

2033
03:32:09,972 --> 03:32:14,000
Now, Mr. Frodo, you shouldn't
make fun. I was being serious.

2034
03:32:15,111 --> 03:32:16,477
So was I.

2035
03:32:25,388 --> 03:32:28,050
"Samwise the Brave."

2036
03:32:32,361 --> 03:32:33,692
Smeagol?

2037
03:32:33,863 --> 03:32:36,764
We're not going to wait for you. Come on.

2038
03:32:36,933 --> 03:32:38,867
Master.

2039
03:32:39,034 --> 03:32:41,935
Master looks after us.

2040
03:32:42,706 --> 03:32:45,504
Master wouldn't hurt us.

2041
03:32:45,674 --> 03:32:48,143
Master broke his promise.

2042
03:32:48,310 --> 03:32:50,471
Don't ask Smeagol.

2043
03:32:50,647 --> 03:32:53,843
Poor, poor Smeagol.

2044
03:32:54,016 --> 03:32:56,850
Master betrayed us.

2045
03:32:57,052 --> 03:33:00,112
Wicked. Tricksy. False.

2046
03:33:00,323 --> 03:33:04,225
We ought to wring his filthy little neck.

2047
03:33:04,394 --> 03:33:07,123
Kill him! Kill him!

2048
03:33:07,297 --> 03:33:08,787
Kill them both!

2049
03:33:08,965 --> 03:33:12,593
And then we take the precious...

2050
03:33:12,769 --> 03:33:16,296
and we be the master!

2051
03:33:16,972 --> 03:33:19,635
But the fat Hobbit, he knows.

2052
03:33:19,809 --> 03:33:22,471
Eyes always watching.

2053
03:33:22,646 --> 03:33:26,207
Then we stabs them out.

2054
03:33:26,382 --> 03:33:30,877
Put out his eyeses and make him crawl.

2055
03:33:31,086 --> 03:33:34,522
Yes. Yes. Yes.

2056
03:33:34,724 --> 03:33:37,420
Kill them both.

2057
03:33:37,593 --> 03:33:39,994
Yes. No! No!

2058
03:33:40,197 --> 03:33:43,894
It's too risky. It's too risky.

2059
03:33:44,601 --> 03:33:47,194
Where is he? Where has he gone?

2060
03:33:47,370 --> 03:33:49,963
- Hey, Gollum! Where are you?
- Smeagol?

2061
03:33:50,139 --> 03:33:55,543
We could let her do it.

2062
03:33:56,513 --> 03:34:00,643
Yes. She could do it.

2063
03:34:00,816 --> 03:34:05,379
Yes, precious, she could.

2064
03:34:05,588 --> 03:34:11,584
And then we takes it once they're dead.

2065
03:34:12,561 --> 03:34:15,395
Once they're dead.

2066
03:34:19,802 --> 03:34:23,500
Come on, Hobbits. Long ways to go yet.

2067
03:34:23,673 --> 03:34:25,731
Smeagol will show you the way.

2068
03:34:25,908 --> 03:34:28,138
Follow me.
